    'draft',
    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"daxxify__sculptra_aesthetic","patient_facing_name":"Long-Lasting Smooth & Rebuild","one_line_positioning":"Daxxify''s extended ~6-month duration means fewer toxin visits per year, while Sculptra supports collagen production over months — a low-visit-count long-term aging plan.","package_goal":"Reduce expression lines with fewer visits and support long-term collagen foundation","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients who want both expression line treatment and structural collagen support, and value reducing total appointment frequency. Patients comfortable with a ~6-month neurotoxin retreatment interval and a multi-session Sculptra series.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients seeking only immediate results, patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or poly-L-lactic acid, patients who cannot commit to the Sculptra multi-session series.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Collagen Loss","Volume Loss","Extended Duration","Facial Aging"],"why_together":"Daxxify addresses dynamic expression lines with ~6-month extended duration; Sculptra stimulates collagen over months. Orthogonal mechanisms; Daxxify''s reduced visit frequency (2/year vs 3-4/year) simplifies scheduling around Sculptra sessions.","A_solves":"Daxxify relaxes the muscles causing dynamic expression lines with approximately twice the duration of traditional neurotoxins — typically ~6 months per treatment.","A_does_not_solve":"Daxxify cannot reverse skin laxity, support collagen production, or address structural volume loss from collagen breakdown.","B_adds":"Sculptra stimulates collagen production gradually over a series of treatments, providing structural support that Daxxify cannot address.","clinical_rationale":"Daxxify''s peptide exchange technology provides ~6-month neurotoxin duration — roughly twice that of traditional neurotoxins. This extended duration changes the treatment plan cadence: patients need only 2 toxin visits per year instead of 3-4, which simplifies scheduling around Sculptra sessions and reduces total appointment burden. These address two fundamentally different aspects of aging — movement-caused lines and collagen/volume loss — through completely different mechanisms and timelines. Note: No published controlled trial data exists for this specific combination. The FDA Sculptra label states that safety and effectiveness in combination with other products have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.","patient_education_summary":"Daxxify is a newer neurotoxin that smooths expression lines and typically lasts about six months — roughly twice as long as traditional options. But expression lines are only part of what changes with age. Over time, you lose the collagen that supports your facial structure. Sculptra works gradually over months to support collagen production. Your provider may suggest using both, depending on your needs — Daxxify handles lines from muscle movement, Sculptra supports the structure underneath. This combination is used in clinical practice, but it has not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials, so your provider can discuss whether it makes sense for your individual situation.","staff_close":"When a patient values fewer visits and long-term structural improvement: ''There are two different things happening with aging. The lines from expressions — that''s what Daxxify addresses. It uses a peptide formulation that tends to last about six months, so you''d come in roughly twice a year for that instead of three or four times. The loss of fullness and firmness is from collagen breakdown over time — Sculptra addresses that gradually.''","staff_talking_points":"The unique angle for Daxxify + Sculptra is visit efficiency: 2 Daxxify visits/year vs 3-4 for traditional neurotoxins, combined with a Sculptra series that''s already multi-session. This framing resonates with patients who find frequent appointments burdensome. Daxxify contains no human or animal byproducts — relevant for some patients. This combination has not been evaluated in controlled trials; staff should present it as a provider-recommended option, not a standard bundle.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not guarantee Daxxify duration at exactly 6 months — duration varies by patient and it ''typically lasts about 6 months for many patients'' per FDA labeling; individual results vary.","Do not describe Sculptra results as immediate — Sculptra builds gradually over months.","Do not state the combination is FDA approved as a package — the FDA Sculptra label explicitly notes combination use not evaluated in controlled clinical trials.","Do not describe Sculptra as a ''filler'' — it is a biostimulator; it stimulates collagen, it does not fill space."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Daxxify already costs more than regular Botox. Adding Sculptra seems like a lot.","handling_language":"They''re addressing two different things, so it''s really a separate decision. Daxxify for fewer toxin visits and Sculptra for structural support are both independent options — you don''t need to decide on both at once. Your provider can help you prioritize based on what concerns you most right now.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t bundle-push. Let the clinical rationale speak rather than the cost-per-outcome argument."},{"objection_type":"timeline","patient_says":"Daxxify lasts 6 months and Sculptra takes months to work — this is a long commitment.","handling_language":"That''s accurate, and it''s worth thinking through. Daxxify means fewer neurotoxin visits — about twice a year. Sculptra requires an initial series of 2-3 sessions and then annual maintenance. So this is a longer-term plan. Many patients find the reduced visit frequency to be one of the appealing parts — it consolidates a lot of their maintenance into a predictable rhythm.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t minimize the time commitment. Sculptra is a real multi-session investment."},{"objection_type":"daxxify_novelty","patient_says":"I haven''t tried Daxxify yet. Should I start with something I know first?","handling_language":"That''s completely reasonable. Many patients prefer to try Daxxify first on its own to see how they respond before adding Sculptra. There''s no requirement to start both at the same time. Your provider can advise on the right starting point for your goals.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t push Daxxify to patients who are Botox-loyal. Let the provider guide that decision."},{"objection_type":"safety_concern","patient_says":"Is it safe to do Daxxify and Sculptra together?","handling_language":"This combination is used in clinical practice. The FDA Sculptra label notes that combination use with other products hasn''t been formally studied in controlled trials, which is why your provider assesses whether it''s appropriate for you individually rather than recommending it as a routine protocol. Your provider can explain their reasoning.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''completely safe'' without the FDA caveat acknowledgment."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me start with just Daxxify today.","handling_language":"Of course. Many patients start with the neurotoxin and revisit structural conversations at a future visit. We can do Daxxify today and circle back on Sculptra whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t reopen the Sculptra conversation after the patient has indicated they want to pause."}],"sequencing_note":"Same session or staggered. Some providers prefer to establish Sculptra series first, then layer Daxxify for dynamic lines. If sequential: Daxxify can be done at any point in the Sculptra series.","timing_note":"Long-term plan: Daxxify every 5-6 months; Sculptra series of 2-3 sessions 4-6 weeks apart, then annual maintenance. Reduced toxin visit frequency (2/year) simplifies combined scheduling.","downtime_note":"Daxxify: minimal, full effect visible within days. Sculptra: injection site swelling and bruising possible; Sculptra 5-5-5 massage protocol required post-treatment. Sculptra results build over months — not immediate.","same_session_ok":"conditional — same session performed in clinical practice; FDA Sculptra label notes combination use not evaluated in controlled clinical trials; provider should discuss caveat with patient","maintenance_story":"Daxxify every 5-6 months (2 visits/year); Sculptra series of 2-3 sessions 4-6 weeks apart for initial treatment, then annual maintenance. The reduced toxin visit frequency is a practical benefit when coordinating a multi-treatment plan.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Daxxify follow-up, if you''re interested in discussing structural support, we can revisit the Sculptra conversation at that visit.","next_visit_prompt":"Sculptra structural support is worth discussing at your Daxxify maintenance visit if long-term collagen support is a goal.","source_support_summary":"FDA Sculptra Aesthetic labeling: indicated for correction of shallow to deep nasolabial fold contour deficiencies and other facial wrinkles. ''The safety and effectiveness of SCULPTRA Aesthetic used in combination with other products and procedures have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.'' FDA label — Daxxify: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; peptide exchange technology for ~6-month duration; no human or animal byproducts. Expert consensus: supports neurotoxin + biostimulator combinations based on orthogonal mechanisms at different tissue depths.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    NOW(),
    NOW()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM agent_fuel_documents
    WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
      AND content->>'pair_key' = 'daxxify__sculptra_aesthetic'
);

