alignment in loyalty programs and training. These address two fundamentally different aspects of aging — movement-caused lines and collagen/volume loss — through completely different mechanisms and timelines. Note: No published controlled trial data exists for this specific combination. The FDA Sculptra label states that safety and effectiveness in combination with other products have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.","patient_education_summary":"Dysport smooths the lines caused by facial expressions — it works quickly, usually within a couple of days, and has a natural spread that works well for broader areas like your forehead. But expression lines are only part of what changes with age. Over time, you also lose the collagen that gives your face its structure. Sculptra works gradually over months to support collagen production. Your provider may suggest using both, depending on your situation — Dysport handles what your muscles are doing on the surface, Sculptra supports what''s underneath. This combination is used in clinical practice, but it has not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials, so your provider can discuss whether it makes sense for you.","staff_close":"When a patient is concerned about both expression lines and overall facial structure: ''There are really two different things happening. The lines around your eyes and across your forehead are from muscle movement — Dysport addresses that, and it tends to spread nicely for a natural look over broader areas. But the overall loss of fullness and firmness is from collagen breaking down over time. Sculptra works gradually to support collagen production.''","staff_talking_points":"Dysport''s faster onset (2-3 days) vs Sculptra''s gradual months-long collagen build creates a useful contrast when explaining timelines: ''You''ll see the Dysport working within a few days; Sculptra works in the background over months.'' Both are Galderma products — worth mentioning for practices with Aspire loyalty alignment. Staff should not present this as a standard protocol — it is a provider-recommended option that has not been evaluated in controlled trials.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not describe Sculptra results as immediate or fast — Sculptra works gradually over months.","Do not state the combination is FDA approved as a package — the FDA Sculptra label explicitly notes combination use not evaluated in controlled trials.","Do not describe Sculptra as a ''filler'' — it is a biostimulator, not a volume-filling product.","Do not oversell the Galderma ecosystem angle as a clinical benefit — it is a practice logistics consideration, not a clinical efficacy advantage."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Dysport for now?","handling_language":"Absolutely. These are independent treatments for different concerns. Dysport handles the expression lines now; Sculptra is a longer-term structural conversation you can have whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t create urgency around when to start Sculptra."},{"objection_type":"timeline","patient_says":"How quickly will I see results from each?","handling_language":"Dysport typically shows results within 2-3 days — you''ll see the expression lines softening quickly. Sculptra is different — it works by gradually stimulating collagen production over weeks and months. Most patients complete 2-3 Sculptra sessions 4-6 weeks apart and notice gradual improvement over the following months. They''re on very different timelines, which is part of why they complement each other.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t overstate Sculptra timeline — don''t say ''you''ll see results in a few weeks.''"},{"objection_type":"safety_concern","patient_says":"Is it safe to do both?","handling_language":"This combination is used in clinical practice. The FDA Sculptra label does note that combination use with other products hasn''t been formally studied in controlled trials. Your provider evaluates whether it''s appropriate for your individual situation.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the FDA caveat."},{"objection_type":"dysport_preference","patient_says":"I like Dysport because it spreads naturally. Does Sculptra change that?","handling_language":"Sculptra works in a completely different layer and through a different mechanism — it stimulates your collagen, not your muscles. It doesn''t interact with how Dysport spreads or works. They''re genuinely independent treatments that happen to be from the same manufacturer.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t imply there''s any clinical interaction between Dysport and Sculptra that would change Dysport''s diffusion properties."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"I''ll think about Sculptra for another time.","handling_language":"That makes sense. We can do Dysport today and keep the Sculptra conversation open for whenever you''re ready to revisit it.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t reopen the Sculptra close after the patient declines."}],"sequencing_note":"Same session or staggered. Some providers prefer to establish Sculptra series first, then layer Dysport. If sequential: Dysport can be done at any point in the Sculptra series.","timing_note":"Long-term plan: Dysport every 3-4 months; Sculptra series of 2-3 sessions 4-6 weeks apart, then annual maintenance. Dysport''s faster onset (2-3 days) means patients see initial results quickly while Sculptra''s gradual collagen build progresses.","downtime_note":"Dysport: minimal, results visible within 2-3 days. Sculptra: injection site swelling and bruising possible; massage protocol required. Sculptra results build gradually — not an immediate outcome.","same_session_ok":"conditional — same session performed in clinical practice; FDA Sculptra label notes combination use not evaluated in controlled clinical trials; provider should discuss caveat with patient","maintenance_story":"Dysport every 3-4 months; Sculptra series of 2-3 sessions 4-6 weeks apart for initial treatment, then annual maintenance. Galderma ecosystem alignment may simplify loyalty program tracking for practices using both Aspire and Aspire.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Dysport follow-up, if you''d like to discuss the structural support piece, we can revisit Sculptra at that time.","next_visit_prompt":"If long-term collagen support becomes a goal, we can discuss Sculptra at your next Dysport visit or at any time.","source_support_summary":"FDA Sculptra Aesthetic labeling: ''The safety and effectiveness of SCULPTRA Aesthetic used in combination with other products and procedures have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.'' FDA label — Dysport: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; broader diffusion pattern, faster onset (2-3 days). Expert consensus: supports neurotoxin + biostimulator combinations based on orthogonal mechanisms. Galderma ecosystem: both Dysport and Sculptra are Galderma products.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
