    'pairing_fuel',
    'draft',
    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"jeuveau__sculptra_aesthetic","patient_facing_name":"Smooth & Rebuild (Jeuveau)","one_line_positioning":"Jeuveau''s aesthetics-only neurotoxin addresses expression lines while Sculptra supports collagen production over months — the same neurotoxin + biostimulator rationale applied to the aesthetics-first toxin.","package_goal":"Reduce expression lines with an aesthetics-only neurotoxin and support long-term collagen structure","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients in Evolus-ecosystem practices who want both expression line treatment with Jeuveau and long-term structural collagen support through Sculptra. Patients who value Jeuveau''s aesthetics-only positioning.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or poly-L-lactic acid, patients who cannot commit to the Sculptra multi-session series.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Collagen Loss","Volume Loss","Facial Aging"],"why_together":"Jeuveau addresses dynamic expression lines through the standard BoNT-A mechanism; Sculptra stimulates collagen production. Orthogonal mechanisms — the same core rationale as all neurotoxin + biostimulator pairings, applied to Jeuveau. Note: Jeuveau-specific combination evidence is more limited than other neurotoxins.","A_solves":"Jeuveau relaxes the muscles causing dynamic expression lines (frown lines, crow''s feet, forehead) through prabotulinumtoxinA neuromodulation.","A_does_not_solve":"Jeuveau cannot reverse collagen loss, support structural volume, or address skin laxity.","B_adds":"Sculptra stimulates collagen production gradually — providing structural support that Jeuveau cannot deliver.","clinical_rationale":"Jeuveau is an aesthetics-only neurotoxin (prabotulinumtoxinA) with an equivalent BoNT-A mechanism to other neurotoxins. The core pairing logic is the same as any neurotoxin + biostimulator combination: they address two fundamentally different aspects of aging through completely different mechanisms. Note: No published controlled trial data exists for this specific combination, and Jeuveau-specific combination evidence is limited. The FDA Sculptra label states that safety and effectiveness in combination with other products have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials. The pairing rationale relies on class-level clinical reasoning for neurotoxin + biostimulator combinations.","patient_education_summary":"Jeuveau is a neurotoxin designed specifically for aesthetics — it smooths the lines caused by facial expressions like frowning or squinting. But expression lines are only part of what changes with age. Over time, you also lose the collagen that supports your facial structure. Sculptra works gradually over months to support collagen production. Your provider may suggest using both, depending on your individual situation. This combination is used in clinical practice, but it has not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials, so your provider can discuss whether it makes sense for you.","staff_close":"The neurotoxin + biostimulator rationale applies to Jeuveau the same way it does to any neurotoxin. ''Jeuveau addresses the lines from muscle movement. Sculptra supports collagen production over time. They work at different depths and on different timelines.'' Present this as an option the provider may recommend based on the patient''s individual needs.","staff_talking_points":"Note that Jeuveau-specific combination evidence is limited compared to other neurotoxins. The pairing rationale is class-level reasoning. Staff should not present this as well-studied — it relies on the general neurotoxin + biostimulator rationale. Jeuveau is an Evolus product; Sculptra is Galderma — cross-brand pairing, different loyalty programs. The aesthetics-only positioning of Jeuveau (''Hi-Pure technology, designed for aesthetics'') is a relevant differentiator worth communicating to patients who appreciate that focus.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not overstate the evidence base for this specific pairing — Jeuveau-specific combination evidence is limited; the rationale is class-level.","Do not describe Sculptra results as immediate — Sculptra works gradually over months.","Do not state the combination is FDA approved as a package — FDA Sculptra label notes combination use not evaluated in controlled trials.","Do not describe Sculptra as a ''filler'' — it is a biostimulator."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Jeuveau today and add Sculptra later if I want?","handling_language":"Absolutely. These are two independent decisions. Many patients start with the neurotoxin and revisit the structural conversation at a future visit.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t push both treatments in the same appointment if the patient is hesitant."},{"objection_type":"jeuveau_novelty","patient_says":"I''ve never tried Jeuveau. How is it different from Botox?","handling_language":"Jeuveau uses the same mechanism as other neurotoxins — it relaxes the muscles that create expression lines. It''s formulated specifically for aesthetic use with Hi-Pure manufacturing technology. Your provider can discuss whether Jeuveau is a good fit for you. The combination with Sculptra we''re discussing today is about the two different things they address — expression lines and collagen support — not specifically about which neurotoxin you use.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t make comparative efficacy claims between Jeuveau and other neurotoxins."},{"objection_type":"safety_concern","patient_says":"Is this combination studied and safe?","handling_language":"This combination is used in clinical practice. The FDA Sculptra label notes that combination use with other products hasn''t been formally studied in controlled trials. Jeuveau-specific combination evidence is also limited — the rationale is based on class-level clinical reasoning for neurotoxin + biostimulator combinations. Your provider can explain whether they recommend this for your situation.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t overstate the evidence. Be honest about the limitations."},{"objection_type":"timeline","patient_says":"How long before I see results from Sculptra?","handling_language":"Sculptra works gradually — most patients complete 2-3 sessions 4-6 weeks apart and notice changes over the following months. It''s a gradual process because it supports your own collagen production rather than adding something immediately visible. Jeuveau, in contrast, shows results within days.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t overstate Sculptra speed. It is genuinely gradual."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me just do Jeuveau for now.","handling_language":"Of course. We''ll do Jeuveau today and the Sculptra conversation can wait until you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t reopen the Sculptra close."}],"sequencing_note":"Same session or staggered. If sequential: Jeuveau can be done at any point in the Sculptra series.","timing_note":"Long-term plan: Jeuveau every 3-4 months; Sculptra series of 2-3 sessions 4-6 weeks apart, then annual maintenance.","downtime_note":"Jeuveau: minimal, results within days. Sculptra: injection site swelling and bruising possible; massage protocol required. Sculptra results build gradually.","same_session_ok":"conditional — same session performed in clinical practice; FDA Sculptra label notes combination use not evaluated in controlled clinical trials; provider should discuss caveat with patient","maintenance_story":"Jeuveau every 3-4 months (Evolus); Sculptra series of 2-3 sessions 4-6 weeks apart, then annual maintenance (Galderma). Different ecosystems — separate loyalty programs.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Jeuveau follow-up, we can revisit the Sculptra structural support conversation if you''re interested.","next_visit_prompt":"Long-term collagen support can be discussed at any future visit when you''re ready to explore it.","source_support_summary":"FDA Sculptra Aesthetic labeling: ''The safety and effectiveness of SCULPTRA Aesthetic used in combination with other products and procedures have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.'' FDA label — Jeuveau: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; aesthetics-only indication; Hi-Pure manufacturing technology. Expert consensus: supports neurotoxin + biostimulator combinations based on orthogonal mechanisms. Note: Jeuveau-specific combination evidence is limited; pairing rationale relies on class-level neurotoxin + biostimulator reasoning.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
