    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"xeomin__sculptra_aesthetic","patient_facing_name":"Pure Smooth & Rebuild","one_line_positioning":"Xeomin''s purified formulation addresses expression lines while Sculptra supports collagen production — a long-term aging plan that some providers consider when protein-free neurotoxin is relevant.","package_goal":"Reduce expression lines with purified neurotoxin and support long-term collagen structure","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients committed to long-term facial aging management who prefer Xeomin''s accessory-protein-free formulation for ongoing neurotoxin use, and want Sculptra''s gradual collagen support as a structural foundation.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or poly-L-lactic acid, patients not committed to long-term treatment, patients who cannot complete the Sculptra series.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Collagen Loss","Volume Loss","Long-Term Aging","Facial Aging"],"why_together":"Xeomin''s accessory-protein-free formulation is a consideration some providers weigh for long-term neurotoxin use; Sculptra''s collagen stimulation is also a long-term structural investment. The combination addresses immediate expression lines and gradual structural support — complementary timelines and mechanisms.","A_solves":"Xeomin relaxes the muscles causing dynamic expression lines. Its purified formulation (incobotulinumtoxinA, no accessory proteins) is a consideration some providers weigh when planning long-term neurotoxin maintenance.","A_does_not_solve":"Xeomin cannot reverse collagen loss, support collagen production, or address structural volume loss.","B_adds":"Sculptra stimulates collagen production over a series of treatments — providing structural support over time that Xeomin cannot deliver.","clinical_rationale":"Xeomin is a purified neurotoxin containing only the active ingredient without accessory proteins. This property is particularly relevant when pairing with Sculptra for long-term aging management plans, since both treatments are used over years. Xeomin is also room-temperature stable, simplifying practice logistics. These address two fundamentally different aspects of aging through completely different mechanisms and timelines. Note: No published controlled trial data exists for this specific combination. The FDA Sculptra label states that safety and effectiveness in combination with other products have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials. The accessory-protein-free formulation does not prevent antibody formation but is a consideration some providers weigh for extended treatment plans.","patient_education_summary":"Xeomin is a purified form of neurotoxin — it contains only the active ingredient without the extra proteins found in some other options. This may matter over the long term because your body is less likely to develop resistance to it. It smooths lines caused by facial expressions. But expression lines are only part of what changes with age. Over time, you lose the collagen that gives your face its structure. Sculptra works gradually over months to support collagen production. Your provider may suggest using both if you''re thinking about a long-term plan for both expression lines and structural support. This combination is used in clinical practice, but it has not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials, so your provider can discuss whether it makes sense for your individual situation.","staff_close":"When discussing Xeomin + Sculptra, the key angle is long-term planning. ''Xeomin is a pure-form neurotoxin — it''s been processed to remove the accessory proteins, which may reduce the chance of your body building resistance over time. That matters when we''re talking about a treatment plan that spans years, combining regular neurotoxin with Sculptra for collagen support. Xeomin handles the expression lines; Sculptra supports the underlying structure.''","staff_talking_points":"For patients already committed to long-term aesthetic maintenance, the accessory-protein-free formulation is a clinical consideration some providers weigh — it does not prevent antibody formation, but some providers find it relevant for extended treatment plans. Staff should present this accurately: ''does not contain accessory proteins, which some providers consider for long-term use'' — not ''prevents resistance.'' This combination is used in clinical practice but has not been evaluated in controlled trials. Xeomin is room-temperature stable (Merz); Sculptra is Galderma — cross-brand. Different loyalty programs.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not claim Xeomin ''prevents'' antibody formation or resistance — the accessory-protein-free formulation does not prevent antibody formation; some providers consider it when long-term immunogenicity is a concern.","Do not describe Sculptra results as immediate — Sculptra works gradually over months.","Do not state the combination is FDA approved as a package — FDA Sculptra label notes combination use not evaluated in controlled trials.","Do not describe Sculptra as a ''filler'' — it is a biostimulator."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Xeomin today?","handling_language":"Of course. These are independent decisions. We can do Xeomin today and revisit the Sculptra conversation whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t create urgency about starting Sculptra."},{"objection_type":"xeomin_differentiation","patient_says":"Why Xeomin specifically? How is it different from regular Botox?","handling_language":"Xeomin contains only the active neurotoxin without the accessory proteins found in some other options. Some providers consider this for long-term neurotoxin users because it doesn''t contain those additional proteins. It also doesn''t require refrigeration. The core mechanism — relaxing the muscles that cause expression lines — is the same. Your provider can discuss whether Xeomin is the right fit for you.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t claim Xeomin is clinically superior to other neurotoxins in efficacy. Don''t say it ''prevents resistance.''"},{"objection_type":"safety_concern","patient_says":"Is this combination studied?","handling_language":"This combination is used in clinical practice. The FDA Sculptra label notes that combination use with other products hasn''t been formally studied in controlled trials. Your provider evaluates whether it''s appropriate for your individual situation.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the FDA caveat."},{"objection_type":"timeline","patient_says":"How long before Sculptra shows results?","handling_language":"Sculptra works gradually — results build over months as your collagen production is stimulated. Most patients need 2-3 sessions spaced 4-6 weeks apart. Xeomin shows results within days. They''re on very different timelines, which is part of why they''re often paired for long-term planning.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t overstate Sculptra speed."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"I want to think about Sculptra before committing.","handling_language":"That makes complete sense — it''s a multi-session commitment. We can do Xeomin today and have the Sculptra conversation whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t press after the patient has asked to pause."}],"sequencing_note":"Same session or staggered. Some providers prefer to establish Sculptra series first, then layer Xeomin. If sequential: Xeomin can be done at any point in the Sculptra series. Xeomin room-temperature storage is a practical logistics benefit.","timing_note":"Long-term plan: Xeomin every 3-4 months; Sculptra series of 2-3 sessions 4-6 weeks apart, then annual maintenance.","downtime_note":"Xeomin: minimal, results within days. Sculptra: injection site swelling and bruising possible; massage protocol required. Sculptra results build gradually over months.","same_session_ok":"conditional — same session performed in clinical practice; FDA Sculptra label notes combination use not evaluated in controlled clinical trials; provider should discuss caveat with patient","maintenance_story":"Xeomin every 3-4 months (Merz); Sculptra series 2-3 sessions 4-6 weeks apart, then annual maintenance (Galderma). Cross-brand combination — separate loyalty programs. Xeomin room-temperature stability is a practice logistics benefit.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Xeomin follow-up, if you''d like to discuss the structural collagen support piece, we can revisit Sculptra at that time.","next_visit_prompt":"When you''re ready to explore long-term structural support, Sculptra is worth discussing at any future appointment.","source_support_summary":"FDA Sculptra Aesthetic labeling: ''The safety and effectiveness of SCULPTRA Aesthetic used in combination with other products and procedures have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.'' FDA label — Xeomin: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; incobotulinumtoxinA; contains no accessory proteins; room-temperature stable. Expert consensus: supports neurotoxin + biostimulator combinations based on orthogonal mechanisms. Note: The accessory-protein-free formulation does not prevent antibody formation; some providers consider it when long-term immunogenicity is a concern.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    NOW(),
    NOW()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM agent_fuel_documents
    WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
      AND content->>'pair_key' = 'xeomin__sculptra_aesthetic'
);

-- Pair 11: Long-Lasting Smooth & Glow (daxxify__skinvive_by_juvederm)
-- Review status: PENDING
-- Tier: combination | Evidence: weak
UPDATE agent_fuel_documents
SET
    content = '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"daxxify__skinvive_by_juvederm","patient_facing_name":"Long-Lasting Smooth & Glow","one_line_positioning":"Daxxify''s ~6-month duration and SKINVIVE''s ~6-month skin quality improvement align on a convenient shared maintenance schedule — addressing expression lines and skin smoothness in two visits per year.","package_goal":"Reduce expression lines with extended duration and improve cheek skin smoothness","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients who value reduced visit frequency (Daxxify''s ~6-month duration) and also want to address overall cheek skin smoothness and skin quality that expression line treatment alone cannot improve.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients seeking traditional volume augmentation (SKINVIVE does not add structural volume), or patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or HA components.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Skin Quality","Skin Smoothness","Extended Duration","Skin Hydration"],"why_together":"Daxxify reduces expression lines with extended ~6-month duration; SKINVIVE improves cheek skin smoothness through intradermal microdroplet HA. Completely different mechanisms at different tissue targets. Both have ~6-month maintenance cycles — a practical scheduling alignment.","A_solves":"Daxxify relaxes the muscles causing expression lines with approximately twice the duration of traditional neurotoxins — typically lasting about 6 months.","A_does_not_solve":"Daxxify cannot improve skin texture, cheek skin smoothness, or overall skin quality — it acts on muscle, not on the skin itself.","B_adds":"SKINVIVE improves cheek skin smoothness through intradermal microdroplet HA hydration — addressing the skin quality that neurotoxin cannot change.","clinical_rationale":"Daxxify''s peptide exchange technology provides ~6-month neurotoxin duration, and SKINVIVE provides approximately 6-month skin quality improvement — creating a convenient shared maintenance schedule. SKINVIVE is NOT a volume filler; it uses microdroplet HA injected intradermally to improve cheek skin smoothness and hydration (evaluated using the FDA''s first clinician-reported glow scale). The combination addresses dynamic wrinkles (Daxxify, fewer annual visits) alongside overall skin quality (SKINVIVE). Daxxify contains no human or animal byproducts. This is a cross-ecosystem pairing (Revance + Allergan). Evidence base is expert consensus from accepted clinical practice; no published controlled trial for this specific pairing exists.","patient_education_summary":"Daxxify is a longer-lasting wrinkle relaxer that works for about six months for many patients, so you may need only about two wrinkle-relaxer visits per year instead of three or four. SKINVIVE is something quite different from a traditional filler — it doesn''t add volume or fill specific lines. Instead, it uses tiny microdroplets of hyaluronic acid just under the skin''s surface to improve your skin''s overall cheek skin smoothness. It also lasts about six months. So if you''re looking for smoother expression lines and healthier-looking skin overall, these two treatments work on completely different aspects of your appearance, and conveniently, they''re on a similar maintenance schedule.","staff_close":"Two key points for this combination. First, clarify what SKINVIVE is: ''SKINVIVE doesn''t add volume the way cheek or lip fillers do. It uses microdroplets to improve the quality and smoothness of your skin itself.'' Second, the scheduling convenience: ''Both Daxxify and SKINVIVE last about six months, so you could potentially schedule maintenance for both on the same visit about twice a year.''","staff_talking_points":"The unique angle for Daxxify + SKINVIVE is the scheduling convenience story: both maintain approximately 6-month durations, which is genuinely rare in aesthetic pairing conversations. Staff should be clear this is a cross-brand pairing (Revance + Allergan) — no shared loyalty programs. Daxxify contains no human or animal byproducts — relevant for some patients. SKINVIVE is not a traditional filler — clarify this proactively with any patient who conflates it with cheek or lip filler.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not describe SKINVIVE as adding volume — it is an intradermal microdroplet product for skin quality, not volumization.","Do not guarantee Daxxify duration at exactly 6 months — it ''typically lasts about 6 months for many patients''; individual variation applies.","Do not describe SKINVIVE''s indication beyond cheek skin smoothness — the FDA indication is specifically for cheek skin smoothness in adults over 21.","Do not overstate the evidence for this combination — the evidence base is expert consensus only; no published controlled trial exists for BoNT-A + microdroplet HA."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Do I have to do both? Can I just do Daxxify?","handling_language":"Of course. These treat completely different things — you can do either one independently. Many patients start with the neurotoxin and consider SKINVIVE at a future visit. There''s no requirement to do both at once.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t create urgency around adding SKINVIVE."},{"objection_type":"skinvive_confusion","patient_says":"Is SKINVIVE a filler? I don''t want more filler.","handling_language":"SKINVIVE is different from traditional fillers. It doesn''t add volume the way cheek or lip fillers do. It uses very small microdroplets of hyaluronic acid placed just under the skin''s surface to improve cheek skin smoothness — it''s more like a skin quality treatment than a volume treatment.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the concern. Clarify the distinction clearly."},{"objection_type":"scheduling_alignment","patient_says":"You mentioned both last about 6 months — can I really do both at the same visit?","handling_language":"In most cases, yes — both can be done in the same appointment, with the neurotoxin first and SKINVIVE following. The maintenance schedules align well, so patients often find it convenient to schedule renewals together. Your provider would confirm whether same-session administration makes sense for you.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t guarantee same-session availability without provider confirmation."},{"objection_type":"daxxify_novelty","patient_says":"I''ve never tried Daxxify. Should I stick with what I know?","handling_language":"That''s a completely reasonable approach. Many patients prefer to try Daxxify independently first before adding anything else. The combination conversation can always happen at a future visit once you''ve seen how Daxxify works for you.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t push Daxxify to reluctant patients. The Botox + SKINVIVE conversation is always an alternative."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me think about the SKINVIVE part.","handling_language":"Of course. We can proceed with Daxxify today and revisit SKINVIVE whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t reopen the SKINVIVE close after the patient indicates they want to pause."}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin administered first, SKINVIVE microdroplets second. SKINVIVE is typically a finishing step as it addresses the skin surface layer.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. Both Daxxify and SKINVIVE have ~6-month maintenance cycles — a convenient scheduling alignment. SKINVIVE microdroplets do not interact with neurotoxin placement.","downtime_note":"Both treatments: minimal. Temporary redness or minor swelling at injection sites possible. Daxxify: results within days. SKINVIVE: results from intradermal microdroplet placement; minimal visible downtime.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Daxxify every 5-6 months; SKINVIVE every 6 months. The shared ~6-month maintenance cycle is a genuine scheduling convenience — patients can often align both renewals in a single annual or semi-annual visit.","rebooking_trigger":"When you come back for your Daxxify renewal, SKINVIVE renewal would be around the same time — we can schedule both together if you''d like.","next_visit_prompt":"At your Daxxify renewal, if you''d like to renew SKINVIVE at the same time, that''s a natural combination for a single visit.","source_support_summary":"FDA label — Daxxify: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; peptide exchange technology for ~6-month duration; no human or animal byproducts (Revance). FDA label — SKINVIVE by Juvederm: indicated for improvement of cheek skin smoothness in adults over 21; microdroplet intradermal HA; not a volume filler (Allergan). Accepted clinical practice: BoNT-A and intradermal HA microdroplet products target different mechanisms; neurotoxin-first sequencing is standard. No published controlled trial for BoNT-A + microdroplet HA combination.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    status  = 'draft'
WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
  AND content->>'pair_key' = 'daxxify__skinvive_by_juvederm';

-- Pair 12: Fast Smooth & Glow (dysport__skinvive_by_juvederm)
-- Review status: PENDING
-- Tier: combination | Evidence: weak
UPDATE agent_fuel_documents
SET
    content = '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"dysport__skinvive_by_juvederm","patient_facing_name":"Fast Smooth & Glow","one_line_positioning":"Dysport''s fast-onset broad coverage addresses expression lines while SKINVIVE improves cheek skin smoothness — wrinkle relaxation and skin quality as two distinct goals.","package_goal":"Reduce expression lines across the upper face and improve cheek skin smoothness","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients who prefer Dysport''s fast onset and natural spread for upper-face lines AND want to address overall cheek skin smoothness and skin quality in a complementary treatment plan.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients seeking traditional volume augmentation, patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or HA components.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Skin Quality","Skin Smoothness","Forehead Lines","Skin Hydration"],"why_together":"Dysport''s broader diffusion treats dynamic expression lines across the upper face (forehead, crow''s feet) quickly; SKINVIVE improves cheek skin smoothness through intradermal microdroplet HA. They address different tissues, different concerns, through different mechanisms.","A_solves":"Dysport relaxes the muscles causing expression lines with broader diffusion for larger treatment areas (forehead, lateral canthal region) and faster clinical onset at 2-3 days.","A_does_not_solve":"Dysport cannot improve skin texture, cheek skin smoothness, or overall skin quality — it acts on muscle.","B_adds":"SKINVIVE improves cheek skin smoothness through intradermal microdroplet HA — addressing the skin quality that Dysport cannot change.","clinical_rationale":"Dysport''s broader diffusion pattern treats dynamic expression lines across the upper face with faster onset (2-5 days). SKINVIVE is a fundamentally different product — NOT a volume filler. SKINVIVE uses microdroplet HA injected intradermally to improve cheek skin smoothness and hydration. It was evaluated using the FDA''s first-ever clinician-reported glow scale. This combination addresses dynamic wrinkles (Dysport) alongside overall skin quality (SKINVIVE) — two complementary but distinct aesthetic goals. Cross-ecosystem pairing (Galderma + Allergan). Evidence base is expert consensus from accepted clinical practice; no published controlled trial for this specific pairing.","patient_education_summary":"Dysport relaxes the muscles that create expression lines like forehead wrinkles and crow''s feet — it works well across broad areas and you may see improvement within a few days. SKINVIVE is something different from a traditional filler — it doesn''t add volume or fill lines. Instead, it uses tiny microdroplets of hyaluronic acid placed just under the skin''s surface to improve your skin''s overall cheek skin smoothness. Think of Dysport as addressing specific wrinkles, and SKINVIVE as improving the quality of the skin itself. If you''re looking for both smoother expressions and healthier-looking skin, these treat two different things.","staff_close":"When explaining this pairing: ''Dysport addresses the expression lines on your forehead and around your eyes by relaxing the muscles that cause them. SKINVIVE does something completely different — it uses microdroplets of hyaluronic acid placed just under the surface to improve skin smoothness. It''s more like a skin quality treatment than a filler.''","staff_talking_points":"SKINVIVE is not a filler in the traditional sense — proactively clarify this to prevent patient confusion. The SKINVIVE + Dysport pairing is a cross-ecosystem combination (Galderma + Allergan) — no shared loyalty programs. Dysport''s faster onset (2-3 days) is a differentiator worth communicating: patients who have had Botox may notice results faster with Dysport. Dysport''s broader diffusion makes it a good conversation for patients with forehead and lateral face concerns. Both products address completely different things — staff should be comfortable explaining this without any feeling of upselling.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not describe SKINVIVE as adding volume — it is an intradermal microdroplet product for skin quality improvement, not volumization.","Do not describe SKINVIVE''s indication beyond cheek skin smoothness — the FDA indication is specifically for cheek skin smoothness in adults over 21.","Do not overstate the evidence for this combination — expert consensus only; no published controlled trial.","Do not imply Dysport''s broader diffusion ''leaks'' into unwanted areas in a way that would concern patients — diffusion is a clinical property managed by provider technique."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Dysport today?","handling_language":"Of course. These are independent treatments for different things. Dysport today is a complete treatment for expression lines. SKINVIVE is a separate decision you can make any time.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t imply Dysport alone is incomplete."},{"objection_type":"skinvive_confusion","patient_says":"I already get filler — do I need something else?","handling_language":"SKINVIVE is actually different from the filler you may already have. It doesn''t add volume to specific areas. Instead, it uses microdroplets placed in the skin itself to improve cheek skin smoothness and hydration — a skin quality improvement rather than a volumizing treatment. If you''re already happy with your filler for volume, SKINVIVE addresses something different.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t imply traditional filler is inadequate. Clarify that these are non-overlapping treatments."},{"objection_type":"dysport_diffusion_concern","patient_says":"I heard Dysport spreads more than other options. Is that a problem?","handling_language":"Dysport does have a broader diffusion pattern, which your provider uses intentionally when treating larger areas like your forehead — it creates a natural, even result. Your provider controls placement and dosing based on your anatomy. The broader diffusion is a feature, not a limitation, when used by an experienced injector in the right areas.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the diffusion concern. Explain it as a provider-controlled property."},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"If I do both at once, will I have more downtime?","handling_language":"Both treatments have minimal downtime — temporary redness and minor swelling are possible at injection sites for each. Combining them in one visit means more injection sites, so some patients prefer to space them out. If you have a specific event coming up, we can plan around that.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''no downtime.'' Be honest about temporary redness and swelling."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me think about SKINVIVE and focus on Dysport today.","handling_language":"That works perfectly. We''ll do Dysport today and keep the SKINVIVE conversation for whenever you''d like to revisit it.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t reopen the SKINVIVE conversation after the patient asks to pause."}],"sequencing_note":"Dysport administered first, SKINVIVE microdroplets second. SKINVIVE is typically a finishing step. Unlike traditional fillers, SKINVIVE microdroplets do not interact with neurotoxin placement.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. If sequential: neurotoxin 2 weeks before SKINVIVE. Dysport retreatment at 3-4 months; SKINVIVE retreatment approximately every 6 months.","downtime_note":"Dysport: minimal, results visible within 2-3 days. SKINVIVE: minimal, intradermal microdroplet placement. Both: temporary redness and minor swelling at injection sites possible.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Dysport every 3-4 months; SKINVIVE every 6 months. Patients on Dysport maintenance can align one SKINVIVE renewal with approximately every other Dysport visit.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Dysport follow-up, if you''d like to discuss SKINVIVE, that''s a natural time to have that conversation.","next_visit_prompt":"If skin quality is a goal, SKINVIVE can be discussed at any future visit or at your next Dysport renewal.","source_support_summary":"FDA label — Dysport: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; broader diffusion pattern, faster onset 2-5 days (Galderma). FDA label — SKINVIVE by Juvederm: indicated for improvement of cheek skin smoothness in adults over 21; microdroplet intradermal HA; not a volume filler (Allergan). Accepted clinical practice: BoNT-A neuromodulation combined with HA addresses complementary aspects of facial aging; neurotoxin-first sequencing standard. No published controlled trial for BoNT-A + microdroplet HA.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    status  = 'draft'
WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
  AND content->>'pair_key' = 'dysport__skinvive_by_juvederm';

-- Pair 13: Smooth & Glow (Jeuveau) (jeuveau__skinvive_by_juvederm)
-- Review status: PENDING
-- Tier: combination | Evidence: weak
-- NEW ROW (not seeded by 12-01) — INSERT WHERE NOT EXISTS
INSERT INTO agent_fuel_documents (fuel_type, status, content, created_at, updated_at)
SELECT
    'pairing_fuel',
    'draft',
    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"jeuveau__skinvive_by_juvederm","patient_facing_name":"Smooth & Glow (Jeuveau)","one_line_positioning":"Jeuveau''s aesthetics-only neurotoxin relaxes expression lines while SKINVIVE improves cheek skin smoothness — two newer-generation products addressing different aspects of skin appearance.","package_goal":"Reduce expression lines with aesthetics-focused neurotoxin and improve cheek skin smoothness","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients who prefer Jeuveau''s aesthetics-only positioning for expression line treatment AND want to address overall cheek skin smoothness through SKINVIVE.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients seeking traditional volume augmentation, patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or HA components.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Skin Quality","Skin Smoothness","Skin Hydration"],"why_together":"Jeuveau addresses dynamic expression lines through prabotulinumtoxinA neuromodulation; SKINVIVE improves cheek skin smoothness through intradermal microdroplet HA. Different mechanisms, different tissue targets, no overlap.","A_solves":"Jeuveau relaxes the muscles causing expression lines (frown lines, crow''s feet) — an aesthetics-only neurotoxin using Hi-Pure manufacturing technology.","A_does_not_solve":"Jeuveau cannot improve skin texture, cheek skin smoothness, or overall skin quality.","B_adds":"SKINVIVE improves cheek skin smoothness through intradermal microdroplet HA hydration — the skin quality improvement that Jeuveau cannot address.","clinical_rationale":"Jeuveau (''Newtox'') is an aesthetics-only neurotoxin with Hi-Pure technology, addressing dynamic wrinkles through the standard BoNT-A mechanism. SKINVIVE is NOT a volume filler — it uses microdroplet HA injected intradermally to improve cheek skin smoothness and hydration (evaluated using the FDA''s first clinician-reported glow scale). The combination addresses expression lines (Jeuveau) alongside overall skin quality (SKINVIVE). Both are newer-generation products in their respective categories. Cross-ecosystem pairing (Evolus + Allergan). Evidence base is expert consensus from accepted clinical practice; no published controlled trial for this specific pairing. Jeuveau has limited product-specific published evidence in general.","patient_education_summary":"Jeuveau is a wrinkle relaxer designed specifically for cosmetic use — it relaxes the muscles that create expression lines like frown lines and crow''s feet. SKINVIVE is something quite different. It''s not a traditional filler — it doesn''t add volume or fill specific wrinkles. Instead, it uses tiny microdroplets of hyaluronic acid placed just under the skin''s surface to improve your skin''s overall cheek skin smoothness. If you''re concerned about both specific expression lines and your skin''s overall smoothness, these two treatments work on completely different aspects of your appearance.","staff_close":"Two important things to communicate with this pairing. First, Jeuveau is designed specifically for cosmetic use — it works by relaxing the muscles that cause expression lines. Second, SKINVIVE is not a traditional filler: ''It doesn''t add volume to your cheeks or lips. It uses microdroplets to improve your skin''s overall quality — skin smoothness and hydration.''","staff_talking_points":"Jeuveau is an Evolus product; SKINVIVE is Allergan — different loyalty programs, no shared ecosystem. SKINVIVE was the first product evaluated using an FDA glow scale — a unique differentiator worth mentioning for patients who ask about the science. For patients who ask how Jeuveau compares to other neurotoxins: the mechanism is the same (BoNT-A); Jeuveau''s Hi-Pure technology is its differentiator. Staff should not make comparative efficacy claims between neurotoxins. Let the patient''s concerns guide the conversation.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not describe SKINVIVE as adding volume — it is an intradermal microdroplet product for skin quality improvement, not volumization.","Do not make comparative efficacy claims between Jeuveau and other neurotoxins — the mechanism is the same; the differences are formulation-based.","Do not describe SKINVIVE''s indication beyond cheek skin smoothness — the FDA indication is specifically for cheek skin smoothness in adults over 21.","Do not overstate Jeuveau-specific evidence — published evidence specific to Jeuveau combinations is limited; the pairing rationale is class-level."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I start with just Jeuveau?","handling_language":"Absolutely. These are completely independent decisions. Jeuveau today is a complete treatment for expression lines. SKINVIVE is a separate option you can revisit at any time.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t imply SKINVIVE is necessary."},{"objection_type":"jeuveau_novelty","patient_says":"How is Jeuveau different from Botox?","handling_language":"Jeuveau uses the same core mechanism as other neurotoxins — it relaxes the muscles that create expression lines. It was developed specifically for aesthetic use with Hi-Pure manufacturing technology. Your provider can discuss whether Jeuveau is the right fit for you based on your specific situation and history.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t make comparative efficacy claims between Jeuveau and Botox."},{"objection_type":"skinvive_confusion","patient_says":"What''s the difference between SKINVIVE and regular filler?","handling_language":"SKINVIVE is quite different from traditional fillers. It doesn''t add volume to your cheeks or lips. Instead, it uses tiny microdroplets placed just under the skin''s surface to improve cheek skin smoothness and hydration from within — it''s more like a skin quality treatment. It was the first product evaluated using an FDA glow scale.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t conflate SKINVIVE with traditional volumizing filler."},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"How much downtime if I do both?","handling_language":"Both have minimal downtime — temporary redness or minor swelling at injection sites is possible. Most patients return to their normal routine the same day. Combining them in one visit does mean more injection sites, so if that''s a concern, spacing them out is always an option.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''no downtime.''"},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me just do Jeuveau for now and think about SKINVIVE.","handling_language":"Of course. We can do Jeuveau today and you can bring up SKINVIVE whenever you''re ready to discuss it.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t try to close SKINVIVE after the patient asks to wait."}],"sequencing_note":"Jeuveau administered first, SKINVIVE microdroplets second. SKINVIVE is typically a finishing step.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. If sequential: neurotoxin 2 weeks before SKINVIVE. Jeuveau retreatment at 3-4 months; SKINVIVE retreatment approximately every 6 months.","downtime_note":"Both: minimal. Temporary redness or minor swelling at injection sites possible. Both products: normal activity same day for most patients.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Jeuveau every 3-4 months; SKINVIVE every 6 months. Patients on Jeuveau maintenance can align one SKINVIVE renewal with approximately every other Jeuveau visit.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Jeuveau follow-up, if you''d like to discuss SKINVIVE, we can revisit that conversation.","next_visit_prompt":"SKINVIVE for skin quality improvement can be discussed at your next visit whenever you''re ready.","source_support_summary":"FDA label — Jeuveau: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; aesthetics-only indication; Hi-Pure manufacturing technology (Evolus). FDA label — SKINVIVE by Juvederm: indicated for improvement of cheek skin smoothness in adults over 21; microdroplet intradermal HA; not a volume filler (Allergan). Accepted clinical practice: BoNT-A neuromodulation combined with HA addresses complementary aspects of facial aging; neurotoxin-first sequencing standard. No published controlled trial for BoNT-A + microdroplet HA. Note: Jeuveau-specific combination evidence is limited.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    NOW(),
    NOW()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM agent_fuel_documents
    WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
      AND content->>'pair_key' = 'jeuveau__skinvive_by_juvederm'
