) alongside overall skin quality (SKINVIVE). For patients seeking both expression line relaxation and improved skin quality, these are two complementary but distinct treatments. Xeomin is room-temperature stable. Cross-ecosystem pairing (Merz + Allergan). Evidence base is expert consensus from accepted clinical practice; no published controlled trial for this specific pairing.","patient_education_summary":"Xeomin is a wrinkle relaxer known as the ''pure'' neurotoxin — it contains only the active ingredient without extra proteins, which some providers consider when long-term immunogenicity is a concern. SKINVIVE is quite different from a traditional filler — it doesn''t add volume or fill specific wrinkles. Instead, it uses tiny microdroplets of hyaluronic acid just under the skin''s surface to improve your skin''s overall cheek skin smoothness. If you''re looking for both smoother expression lines and healthier-looking skin overall, these are two different treatments that work on two different aspects of your appearance.","staff_close":"Two distinct stories to communicate. On Xeomin: ''It''s the pure neurotoxin — just the active ingredient without complexing proteins. Some providers consider this for patients planning long-term neurotoxin use, as it does not contain accessory proteins. It also stores at room temperature.'' On SKINVIVE: ''This is not a filler in the traditional sense. SKINVIVE uses microdroplets placed in the skin itself to improve cheek skin smoothness — think of it as a skin quality treatment.''","staff_talking_points":"For patients asking about Xeomin: it does not contain accessory proteins found in some other neurotoxins — some providers consider this when long-term immunogenicity is a concern. Do not say it ''prevents resistance'' — say it ''does not contain the accessory proteins found in some other neurotoxins.'' SKINVIVE was the first product evaluated using an FDA glow scale — a unique educational point. This is a Merz + Allergan cross-ecosystem pairing — different loyalty programs. If patients ask about doing both: ''They work on completely different things. Xeomin relaxes expression lines; SKINVIVE improves the quality of the skin itself. No overlap or redundancy.''","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not claim Xeomin ''prevents'' antibody formation or resistance — the formulation does not contain accessory proteins, which some providers consider when long-term immunogenicity is a concern; this does not prevent antibody formation.","Do not describe SKINVIVE as adding volume — it is an intradermal microdroplet product for skin quality, not volumization.","Do not describe SKINVIVE''s indication beyond cheek skin smoothness — FDA indication is specifically for cheek skin smoothness in adults over 21.","Do not overstate the evidence for this combination — expert consensus only; no published controlled trial."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Xeomin today?","handling_language":"Of course. These are completely independent treatments. Xeomin today for expression lines, and SKINVIVE is a separate conversation you can have whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t make SKINVIVE feel required."},{"objection_type":"xeomin_differentiation","patient_says":"Why Xeomin instead of Botox?","handling_language":"Xeomin uses the same core mechanism as other neurotoxins — relaxing the muscles that cause expression lines. What makes it different is its formulation: it contains only the active neurotoxin without accessory proteins. Some providers consider this for patients planning long-term neurotoxin use. It also stores at room temperature. Your provider can discuss whether Xeomin is the right fit for you.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t claim Xeomin is more effective. Don''t say it prevents resistance."},{"objection_type":"skinvive_confusion","patient_says":"Is SKINVIVE a filler? I''m not looking for more filler.","handling_language":"SKINVIVE is different from traditional fillers. It doesn''t add volume the way cheek or lip fillers do. It uses very small microdroplets placed just under the skin''s surface to improve cheek skin smoothness from within — it''s more like a skin quality treatment. There''s no added volume or structural change.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t conflate SKINVIVE with volumizing filler."},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"How long will I need to recover from both?","handling_language":"Both treatments have minimal downtime — most patients return to normal activity the same day. Temporary redness or minor swelling at injection sites is possible for either treatment. If you have a specific event coming up, we can plan accordingly.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''no downtime'' — be honest about potential temporary effects."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me think about SKINVIVE — can we just do Xeomin today?","handling_language":"Absolutely. Xeomin today, and SKINVIVE is there for whenever you''re ready to revisit it.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t reopen the SKINVIVE close."}],"sequencing_note":"Xeomin administered first, SKINVIVE microdroplets second. SKINVIVE is typically a finishing step. SKINVIVE microdroplets do not interact with neurotoxin placement.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. If sequential: neurotoxin 2 weeks before SKINVIVE. Xeomin retreatment at 3-4 months; SKINVIVE retreatment approximately every 6 months.","downtime_note":"Both: minimal. Temporary redness or minor swelling at injection sites possible. Xeomin: room-temperature stable (practical logistics benefit). Both: normal activity same day for most patients.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Xeomin every 3-4 months; SKINVIVE every 6 months. Patients can align one SKINVIVE renewal with approximately every other Xeomin visit. Xeomin room-temperature stability is a practice logistics benefit.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Xeomin follow-up, if you''d like to add the skin quality piece, we can discuss SKINVIVE at that visit.","next_visit_prompt":"SKINVIVE for cheek skin smoothness can be discussed at any future visit when you''re ready.","source_support_summary":"FDA label — Xeomin: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; incobotulinumtoxinA; no accessory/complexing proteins; room-temperature stable (Merz). FDA label — SKINVIVE by Juvederm: indicated for improvement of cheek skin smoothness in adults over 21; microdroplet intradermal HA; not a volume filler (Allergan). Accepted clinical practice: BoNT-A neuromodulation combined with HA addresses complementary aspects of facial aging; neurotoxin-first sequencing standard. No published controlled trial for BoNT-A + microdroplet HA.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
