    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"juvederm_voluma_xc__sculptra_aesthetic","patient_facing_name":"Rebuild & Contour (Cheek)","one_line_positioning":"Sculptra builds collagen in the midface foundation over months while Voluma provides immediate structural cheek contouring — deep structure from two complementary pathways.","package_goal":"Stimulate collagen foundation and provide immediate cheek contouring","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients with significant midface volume loss wanting both long-term collagen structural support (Sculptra) and immediate cheek contouring definition (Voluma). Patients committed to a sequential treatment plan.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients seeking only immediate contouring results, patients who cannot commit to a Sculptra series, patients hypersensitive to poly-L-lactic acid or HA components.","concern_tags":["Cheek Volume Loss","Midface Aging","Collagen Loss","Volume Loss","Structural Support"],"why_together":"Sculptra addresses the collagen infrastructure supporting the midface; Voluma provides the structural scaffold on top. One works gradually from below; the other provides immediate contour from placement. Different depths, different timelines, different mechanisms.","A_solves":"Sculptra stimulates collagen production in the midface gradually — rebuilding the structural foundation that underlies cheek volume and contour.","A_does_not_solve":"Sculptra cannot provide immediate visible cheek contouring — results build over months.","B_adds":"Voluma provides immediate deep cheek volume and contouring through HA gel scaffold — the structural definition that patients can see right away.","clinical_rationale":"Sculptra stimulates collagen production; Voluma provides structural cheek contouring with immediate HA gel correction. Voluma is a robust HA filler designed for deep cheek volume — it provides the immediate structural contour that Sculptra cannot deliver right away. By establishing Sculptra collagen stimulation first, practices may find patients need less Voluma at each subsequent touch-up, as the collagen support provides a more durable base layer. Note: No published controlled trial data exists for this specific combination. The FDA Sculptra label states that safety and effectiveness in combination with other products have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.","patient_education_summary":"Sculptra works gradually over several months to support collagen production — think of it as strengthening the foundation of your facial structure. Voluma is a filler designed specifically for cheek contouring — it adds precise definition and lift right away. Your provider may suggest starting with Sculptra to build that collagen support, then using Voluma for contouring on top of a stronger base. This combination is used in clinical practice, but it has not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials. Your provider can discuss whether this approach makes sense for your individual situation.","staff_close":"When a patient wants cheek restoration, explain the two layers: ''There''s the underlying structure — the collagen that''s been thinning over time — and then there''s the specific contour and definition you see in the mirror. Sculptra supports that underlying collagen production gradually. Voluma gives you the precise cheek sculpting on top of a stronger foundation.''","staff_talking_points":"This combination is used in clinical practice but has not been evaluated in controlled trials. Allergan (Voluma) and Galderma (Sculptra) are different manufacturers — this is a clinical pairing based on each product''s mechanism. When Sculptra restores underlying collagen structure, patients may need less Voluma over time — worth communicating as a long-term efficiency benefit. Present as an option the provider may recommend based on individual needs.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not describe Sculptra results as immediate — results develop gradually over months.","Do not guarantee that Sculptra will reduce the amount of Voluma needed — this may occur but cannot be guaranteed.","Do not state the combination is FDA approved as a package — FDA Sculptra label notes combination use not evaluated in controlled trials.","Do not describe Sculptra as a ''filler'' — it is a biostimulator."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Voluma for the cheeks?","handling_language":"Absolutely — Voluma is designed exactly for cheek contouring and can be done on its own. Sculptra is a separate consideration for patients who want to also address the collagen structure underneath. Whether that''s worth exploring is a conversation to have with your provider based on your individual goals.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t push both if the patient prefers to start with one."},{"objection_type":"timeline","patient_says":"I want cheek contour now — do I have to wait months for Sculptra?","handling_language":"No — you don''t have to do Sculptra first. Voluma can provide immediate cheek contouring. The sequential approach (Sculptra first, then Voluma) is one way providers approach this — it may mean you need less filler over time. But immediate Voluma contouring is a completely valid starting point.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t insist on Sculptra first if the patient wants immediate results."},{"objection_type":"safety_concern","patient_says":"Is it safe to use both in the same area?","handling_language":"This combination is used in clinical practice at different tissue depths — Sculptra works subdermally, Voluma at the deep fat pad level. The FDA Sculptra label notes that combination use hasn''t been formally evaluated in controlled trials, which is why your provider assesses whether it''s appropriate for your specific situation.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the FDA caveat."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me start with Voluma and think about Sculptra later.","handling_language":"That''s a reasonable approach. Voluma today, and Sculptra can be revisited whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t press Sculptra after the patient asks to pause."}],"sequencing_note":"Sequential staging preferred: Sculptra series first, then Voluma contouring 4-6 weeks after last Sculptra session. Same-session in different tissue planes possible by experienced injectors but not evaluated in controlled trials.","timing_note":"Sculptra series first, then Voluma refinement. Voluma up to 2-year duration; Sculptra collagen effect 2+ years — both long-duration, reducing total visit count.","downtime_note":"Voluma: immediate volume, possible minor swelling at deep injection sites. Sculptra: injection site swelling and bruising; 5-5-5 massage required. Sculptra results build gradually.","same_session_ok":"conditional — same-session in different tissue planes by experienced injectors; FDA Sculptra label caveat applies","maintenance_story":"Voluma every 18-24 months; Sculptra annual maintenance after initial series. Both long-duration — reduced total visit count for committed patients.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Voluma follow-up, we can discuss whether adding Sculptra for structural support makes sense for your long-term goals.","next_visit_prompt":"If you''d like to explore the collagen support piece, Sculptra is worth discussing at any future appointment.","source_support_summary":"FDA Sculptra Aesthetic labeling: ''The safety and effectiveness of SCULPTRA Aesthetic used in combination with other products and procedures have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.'' FDA label — Juvederm Voluma XC: indicated for cheek augmentation in adults over 21; deep placement; up to 2-year duration. Expert consensus: supports biostimulator + HA filler combinations based on orthogonal mechanisms.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    NOW(),
    NOW()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM agent_fuel_documents
    WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
      AND content->>'pair_key' = 'juvederm_voluma_xc__sculptra_aesthetic'
