duct design and aligned loyalty programs. For midface: Sculptra builds the collagen base while Lyft provides the immediate structural contouring. For hands: Sculptra can stimulate collagen in dorsal hand tissue while Lyft provides immediate volume correction to reduce visible tendons and veins. Note: No published controlled trial data exists for this specific combination. The FDA Sculptra label states that safety and effectiveness in combination with other products have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.","patient_education_summary":"Sculptra works gradually over several months to support collagen production — it''s strengthening the foundation. Restylane Lyft is a structural filler that adds immediate definition to your cheeks and midface, and it''s also approved for hands. They''re both made by Galderma. Your provider may suggest building the collagen support with Sculptra first, then using Lyft to add the specific contour and structure you want. If your hands are also a concern, both products can be used there. This combination is used in clinical practice, but it has not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials. Your provider can discuss whether this approach makes sense for your individual situation.","staff_close":"Restylane Lyft + Sculptra is a Galderma ecosystem pairing — same manufacturer. ''Sculptra supports collagen production gradually. Lyft gives you the immediate midface structure — the cheekbone definition and lift. Starting with collagen support means the contouring filler sits on a stronger base and you may need less of it.''","staff_talking_points":"A unique advantage of this pairing: Lyft is FDA-approved for hands, and Sculptra can stimulate hand collagen as well. This makes it a genuine dual-area option for patients with both facial and hand aging concerns. Galderma ecosystem means training and loyalty programs cover both products. This combination is used in clinical practice but has not been evaluated in controlled trials. Present as an option the provider may recommend based on individual needs.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not describe Sculptra results as immediate — results develop gradually.","Do not guarantee that Sculptra will reduce the amount of Lyft needed — this may occur but cannot be guaranteed.","Do not state the combination is FDA approved as a package — FDA Sculptra label notes combination use not evaluated in controlled trials.","Do not describe Sculptra as a ''filler'' — it is a biostimulator."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Lyft for the cheeks today?","handling_language":"Absolutely. Lyft can provide immediate midface volume on its own. Sculptra is a separate consideration for patients wanting to add gradual collagen support. Your provider can guide you on what makes sense for your goals.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t push both if the patient wants to start with one."},{"objection_type":"galderma_synergy","patient_says":"Are these better together because they''re both Galderma?","handling_language":"Being from the same manufacturer means practical things — loyalty program alignment, compatible training. But the clinical reason they work together is that they address different aspects of aging through different mechanisms. Sculptra stimulates your collagen; Lyft restores immediate structural volume. They complement each other for those reasons, not just because of the brand.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t imply Galderma combination is clinically superior to cross-brand combinations — the benefit is logistics, not efficacy."},{"objection_type":"hand_concern","patient_says":"Can these also help with my hands?","handling_language":"Yes — Restylane Lyft actually has an FDA indication specifically for dorsal hand volume loss, which is relatively uncommon among fillers. Sculptra can also be used in the hands for collagen stimulation. If hand rejuvenation is a concern, this combination has genuine relevance there alongside any facial treatment.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t oversell the hand application without provider confirmation for the individual patient."},{"objection_type":"safety_concern","patient_says":"Is it safe to use both?","handling_language":"This combination is used in clinical practice. The FDA Sculptra label notes that combination use with other products hasn''t been formally evaluated in controlled trials — your provider assesses whether it''s appropriate for you.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the FDA caveat."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me start with Lyft and think about Sculptra.","handling_language":"Of course. Lyft today, and Sculptra is an option we can revisit whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t press Sculptra after the patient asks to pause."}],"sequencing_note":"Sequential staging preferred: Sculptra series first, then Lyft structural contouring 4-6 weeks after for refinement. Same-session in different tissue planes possible by experienced injectors but not evaluated in controlled trials.","timing_note":"Sculptra series first, then Lyft refinement. Lyft 12-18 months; Sculptra collagen effect 2+ years. Galderma ecosystem simplifies scheduling and loyalty tracking.","downtime_note":"Lyft: immediate volume, possible minor swelling. Sculptra: injection site swelling/bruising; 5-5-5 massage required. Sculptra results build gradually.","same_session_ok":"conditional — same-session in different tissue planes by experienced injectors; FDA Sculptra label caveat applies","maintenance_story":"Lyft every 12-18 months; Sculptra annual maintenance. Both Galderma — single loyalty program for practices using Aspire.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Lyft follow-up, we can discuss whether adding Sculptra for collagen support makes sense for your long-term plan.","next_visit_prompt":"Sculptra structural support is worth discussing at any future visit when you''re ready to explore it.","source_support_summary":"FDA Sculptra Aesthetic labeling: combination use with other products not evaluated in controlled trials. FDA label — Restylane Lyft: indicated for midface volume deficit and dorsal hand volume loss in adults over 21; dual FDA indication (face + hands) unique among HA fillers; Galderma NASHA technology. Expert consensus: supports biostimulator + HA filler combinations based on orthogonal mechanisms. Galderma ecosystem: both products manufacturer-aligned.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
