    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"rha_redensity__sculptra_aesthetic","patient_facing_name":"Rebuild & Refine (Perioral)","one_line_positioning":"Sculptra builds collagen support in the perioral region over months while RHA Redensity''s resilient HA directly smooths fine lines in this high-movement area.","package_goal":"Stimulate perioral collagen support and correct fine perioral lines with movement-compatible HA","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients with perioral fine lines who want both gradual collagen structural support (Sculptra) and immediate fine-line correction with a flexible filler designed for this dynamic area (RHA Redensity).","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients seeking only immediate perioral correction, patients who cannot commit to a Sculptra series, patients hypersensitive to poly-L-lactic acid or HA components.","concern_tags":["Perioral Lines","Fine Lines","Collagen Loss","Dynamic Area","Lip Lines"],"why_together":"Sculptra addresses the underlying collagen loss in the perioral structure; RHA Redensity''s resilient HA is specifically designed for the dynamic perioral zone, flexing with movement rather than resisting it. Two complementary approaches — deep structural support and surface flexible correction.","A_solves":"Sculptra stimulates collagen production in the perioral region gradually — addressing the structural support loss that allows perioral lines to deepen over time.","A_does_not_solve":"Sculptra cannot provide immediate fine-line correction in dynamic areas — results build gradually.","B_adds":"RHA Redensity provides immediate correction of perioral fine lines using resilient HA technology designed for high-movement areas around the mouth — the immediate correction Sculptra cannot deliver.","clinical_rationale":"Sculptra stimulates deep collagen production; RHA Redensity addresses perioral fine lines — one of the most dynamic areas of the face. RHA Redensity uses resilient HA technology specifically designed to accommodate natural facial movement, which is critical around the mouth where patients talk, smile, and eat constantly. Sculptra provides structural collagen support in the perioral region, while RHA Redensity smooths the fine lines on the surface at a different depth. These work at different depths and for different purposes. Note: No published controlled trial data exists for this specific combination. The FDA Sculptra label states that safety and effectiveness in combination with other products have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.","patient_education_summary":"The fine lines around your mouth are in one of the most active areas of your face — you''re constantly talking, smiling, eating. That''s why they may benefit from a filler that moves naturally with your expressions. RHA Redensity is designed for that — it''s a resilient filler that flexes with your facial movement. But those lines also form partly because the deeper collagen structure in your face has been thinning over time. Sculptra addresses that — it supports collagen production gradually over months. Your provider may suggest building the deeper structure with Sculptra first, then using RHA Redensity to smooth the fine surface lines around your mouth. This combination is used in clinical practice, but it has not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials. Your provider can discuss whether it makes sense for your individual situation.","staff_close":"Perioral lines form for two reasons: the skin is constantly moving there, and the underlying collagen support has thinned over time. ''RHA Redensity is a resilient HA designed for dynamic areas — it smooths those lines while still allowing natural movement. Sculptra supports the deeper collagen production that the perioral region needs.''","staff_talking_points":"When Sculptra restores underlying perioral structure, patients may need less RHA Redensity than if filler were used alone. Worth communicating as a potential long-term efficiency benefit. RHA Redensity is a Revance product (formerly Teoxane); Sculptra is Galderma — cross-manufacturer. This is a clinical pairing based on each product''s specific strength. Present as an option the provider may recommend based on individual needs.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not describe Sculptra results as immediate around the perioral area — results develop gradually.","Do not imply RHA Redensity adds lip volume — it corrects perioral fine lines, not lip augmentation.","Do not state the combination is FDA approved as a package — FDA Sculptra label notes combination use not evaluated in controlled trials.","Do not describe Sculptra as a ''filler'' — it is a biostimulator."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do the filler around my mouth?","handling_language":"Absolutely. RHA Redensity is designed specifically for perioral lines and can be done on its own. Sculptra for deep structural support is an additional option your provider may discuss based on your goals.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t push Sculptra if the patient wants filler only."},{"objection_type":"perioral_complexity","patient_says":"The area around my mouth bruises easily. Is this safe to do both?","handling_language":"That''s worth planning around. The perioral area can bruise more easily for some patients. With both Sculptra and RHA Redensity, there would be injections in or near that zone. Some providers prefer to stage the treatments — Sculptra first, then RHA Redensity at a later visit — which would space out the bruising risk. Your provider can advise based on your specific situation.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the practical bruising concern for the perioral area."},{"objection_type":"safety_concern","patient_says":"Is it safe to use Sculptra near my mouth?","handling_language":"Sculptra has an FDA indication for nasolabial folds, which includes the perioral region. The FDA Sculptra label notes that combination use with other products hasn''t been formally evaluated in controlled trials. Your provider assesses whether this combination is appropriate for your individual situation.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the FDA caveat."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me just do the filler around my mouth today.","handling_language":"Of course. RHA Redensity is a complete perioral treatment on its own. We can discuss Sculptra for deeper structural support at any future visit.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t press Sculptra after the patient indicates they want to proceed with filler alone."}],"sequencing_note":"Sequential staging preferred: Sculptra series first (2-3 sessions), then RHA Redensity perioral 4-6 weeks after last session. Same-session possible at different depths by experienced injectors but not evaluated in controlled trials.","timing_note":"Sculptra series first, then RHA Redensity perioral refinement. RHA Redensity perioral 6-12 months maintenance; Sculptra collagen 2+ years.","downtime_note":"RHA Redensity perioral: possible bruising — perioral area prone to bruising; patients should plan accordingly. Sculptra: injection site swelling/bruising; 5-5-5 massage required. Sculptra results build gradually.","same_session_ok":"conditional — same-session at different depths possible; FDA Sculptra label caveat applies; perioral bruising risk should inform staging decision","maintenance_story":"RHA Redensity perioral every 6-12 months; Sculptra annual maintenance after initial series. Sequential plan — Sculptra establishes foundation, RHA Redensity provides surface refinement.","rebooking_trigger":"At your RHA Redensity follow-up, we can discuss whether Sculptra structural support would benefit the perioral area longer-term.","next_visit_prompt":"If you want to address the deeper collagen structure around the mouth, Sculptra is worth discussing at a future visit.","source_support_summary":"FDA Sculptra Aesthetic labeling: combination use with other products not evaluated in controlled trials. FDA label — RHA Redensity: indicated for perioral area correction of dynamic perioral rhytids in adults over 22; resilient HA technology for dynamic areas. Expert consensus: supports biostimulator + HA filler combinations based on orthogonal mechanisms.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
