    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"skinvive_by_juvederm__sculptra_aesthetic","patient_facing_name":"Deep Rebuild & Surface Glow","one_line_positioning":"Sculptra builds collagen from deep structural layers while SKINVIVE improves surface skin quality — an inside-out layered approach to skin aging.","package_goal":"Stimulate deep collagen structure and improve surface skin smoothness and hydration","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients wanting both long-term structural collagen improvement (Sculptra) and surface skin quality enhancement (SKINVIVE cheek smoothness). Patients thinking about comprehensive skin health from different layers.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients seeking only structural volume correction or only surface skin quality, patients who cannot commit to a Sculptra series, patients hypersensitive to poly-L-lactic acid or HA components.","concern_tags":["Collagen Loss","Skin Quality","Skin Smoothness","Volume Loss","Skin Hydration"],"why_together":"Sculptra works subdermally to stimulate collagen from deep within; SKINVIVE works intradermally to improve surface skin quality. Different layers, different purposes — structural foundation and surface finishing.","A_solves":"Sculptra stimulates collagen production in the deep subdermal layer — the foundation supporting facial structure — gradually over months.","A_does_not_solve":"Sculptra cannot improve surface skin texture, hydration, or cheek skin smoothness — it acts deep, not at the skin surface.","B_adds":"SKINVIVE improves cheek skin smoothness through intradermal microdroplet HA — addressing the surface skin quality that Sculptra''s deep action cannot reach.","clinical_rationale":"Sculptra stimulates deep collagen production; SKINVIVE improves skin surface quality through microdroplet HA hydration. These are fundamentally different products working at different depths for different purposes. SKINVIVE is NOT a volume filler — it is a skin quality treatment that improves hydration, smoothness, and overall quality in the dermal layer. Sculptra works subdermally to stimulate collagen production for structural support. Together they represent an inside-out approach: Sculptra builds the foundation from the deep layer, SKINVIVE adds the finishing surface quality on top. Note: No published controlled trial data exists for this specific combination. The FDA Sculptra label states that safety and effectiveness in combination with other products have not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials.","patient_education_summary":"Sculptra and SKINVIVE work at completely different levels of your skin for different reasons. Sculptra goes deep — it gradually supports collagen production that gives your face its underlying structure. That takes a few months to fully develop. SKINVIVE is a surface treatment — it''s not a filler for volume. Instead, it uses tiny microdroplets of hyaluronic acid in the upper layers of your skin to improve hydration, smoothness, and overall skin quality. Your provider may suggest doing a Sculptra series first to build the structure, then adding SKINVIVE as a finishing step for skin quality on the surface. This combination is used in clinical practice, but it has not been evaluated in controlled clinical trials. Your provider can discuss whether this approach makes sense for your individual situation.","staff_close":"SKINVIVE is NOT a volume filler — this is important to communicate clearly. ''Sculptra and SKINVIVE do completely different things at different depths. Sculptra supports collagen production deep in your skin — the foundation. SKINVIVE improves the surface — hydration, smoothness, skin quality. One is structural, the other is finishing.''","staff_talking_points":"The approach is usually Sculptra first to build the foundation, then SKINVIVE as the final step. Don''t describe SKINVIVE as volume correction or contouring — it''s microdroplet HA for skin quality. Allergan (SKINVIVE) and Galderma (Sculptra) are different manufacturers — this is a clinical pairing based on depth and purpose. This combination is used in clinical practice but has not been evaluated in controlled trials. Present as an option the provider may recommend.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not describe Sculptra results as immediate — results develop gradually over months.","Do not describe SKINVIVE as adding volume — it is a skin quality treatment, not a volumizer.","Do not state the combination is FDA approved as a package — FDA Sculptra label notes combination use not evaluated in controlled trials.","Do not describe Sculptra as a ''filler'' — it is a biostimulator."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do one of these?","handling_language":"Absolutely — each can be done independently. They address completely different things at different depths. Your provider can help you prioritize based on what concerns you most right now.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t push the combination if the patient wants to start with one treatment."},{"objection_type":"skinvive_confusion","patient_says":"Is SKINVIVE like Sculptra — does it help with collagen?","handling_language":"They''re quite different. Sculptra works deep to stimulate your body''s own collagen production — it''s a structural treatment. SKINVIVE works in the surface layer of your skin to improve hydration and smoothness using tiny microdroplets of hyaluronic acid. SKINVIVE doesn''t stimulate collagen — it hydrates and improves skin quality at the surface. They complement each other because they work at different depths.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t confuse or conflate the two mechanisms. They are genuinely different."},{"objection_type":"safety_concern","patient_says":"Is it safe to use both?","handling_language":"This combination is used in clinical practice at different tissue depths — Sculptra subdermally, SKINVIVE intradermally. The FDA Sculptra label notes that combination use hasn''t been formally evaluated in controlled trials. Your provider assesses whether it''s appropriate for your situation.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the FDA caveat."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me start with just one.","handling_language":"Of course — both can be done independently. Whichever concern feels most pressing to you now is a good place to start.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t press for the combination after the patient asks to decide one at a time."}],"sequencing_note":"Sequential staging preferred: Sculptra series first to build collagen foundation, then SKINVIVE as finishing step once collagen stimulation is established. Logical layering: deep foundation first, surface finishing second.","timing_note":"Sculptra series first, then SKINVIVE. SKINVIVE ~6 months; Sculptra collagen 2+ years. SKINVIVE renewals can align with Sculptra annual maintenance visits.","downtime_note":"SKINVIVE: minimal, intradermal microdroplet placement. Sculptra: injection site swelling/bruising; 5-5-5 massage required. Sculptra results build gradually.","same_session_ok":"conditional — different tissue depths (subdermal Sculptra, intradermal SKINVIVE); FDA Sculptra label caveat applies","maintenance_story":"SKINVIVE every 6 months; Sculptra annual maintenance. SKINVIVE renewal can be scheduled alongside Sculptra annual maintenance visits. Different manufacturers — separate loyalty programs.","rebooking_trigger":"At your SKINVIVE renewal, we can discuss whether starting Sculptra for structural support makes sense at that time.","next_visit_prompt":"If deep structural collagen support becomes a goal, Sculptra is worth discussing at any future visit.","source_support_summary":"FDA Sculptra Aesthetic labeling: combination use with other products not evaluated in controlled trials. FDA label — SKINVIVE by Juvederm: indicated for improvement of cheek skin smoothness in adults over 21; intradermal microdroplet HA; not a volume filler. Expert consensus: supports layered approaches to skin aging based on deep structural stimulation and superficial hydration addressing different tissue depths.","evidence_level":"weak","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    NOW(),
    NOW()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM agent_fuel_documents
    WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
      AND content->>'pair_key' = 'skinvive_by_juvederm__sculptra_aesthetic'
);

-- Pair 20: Long-Lasting Smooth & Restore (daxxify__juvederm_vollure_xc)
-- Review status: PENDING
-- Tier: combination | Evidence: moderate
UPDATE agent_fuel_documents
SET
    content = '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"daxxify__juvederm_vollure_xc","patient_facing_name":"Long-Lasting Smooth & Restore","one_line_positioning":"Daxxify''s extended-duration neuromodulation reduces annual visit frequency while Vollure addresses the nasolabial fold volume loss that neurotoxin cannot correct.","package_goal":"Reduce expression lines and soften nasolabial folds with a lower-visit maintenance schedule","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients with dynamic upper-face wrinkles and moderate-to-severe nasolabial folds who value longer intervals between neurotoxin treatments and want to address both concerns.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or HA components. Patients seeking only one treatment modality.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Nasolabial Folds","Volume Loss","Fine Lines","Facial Aging"],"why_together":"Daxxify addresses movement-caused lines through neuromodulation with approximately 6-month duration; Vollure restores mid-depth volume in the nasolabial folds that muscle relaxation cannot correct. They operate at different tissue layers and on different aging mechanisms.","A_solves":"Daxxify relaxes the muscles that create dynamic expression lines (forehead, crow''s feet, glabellar lines) with extended duration reducing annual visits from 3-4 to approximately 2.","A_does_not_solve":"Daxxify cannot restore lost volume or soften lines that remain at rest when the face is relaxed.","B_adds":"Vollure restores mid-depth volume in the nasolabial folds and moderate facial lines that persist even when the face is at rest — volume loss that neurotoxin cannot address regardless of duration.","clinical_rationale":"Daxxify uses peptide exchange technology to achieve approximately 6-month duration — roughly double that of traditional neurotoxins — reducing annual neurotoxin visits from 3-4 to approximately 2. It contains no human or animal byproducts. Vollure''s VYCROSS-crosslinked HA addresses nasolabial folds and moderate facial lines with an 18-month duration. The maintenance schedules align well: Daxxify every ~6 months and Vollure every 12-18 months means fewer total office visits compared to traditional neurotoxin + filler plans. Category-level evidence supports BoNT-A + HA filler combinations (DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754); no product-specific study exists for this cross-brand pair. This is a cross-ecosystem pairing (Revance + Allergan).","patient_education_summary":"Daxxify is a newer neurotoxin that works like other wrinkle relaxers but uses a unique peptide technology that helps it last longer — about six months for many patients, compared to three to four months for traditional options. That means fewer maintenance visits for the wrinkle-relaxing portion of your treatment. Vollure is a filler designed specifically for the nasolabial fold lines — those deeper lines from your nose to your mouth — and typically lasts about 18 months. If you''re noticing both expression lines and those deeper smile-line folds, Daxxify addresses the movement-based lines while Vollure addresses the volume-based lines. The longer duration of Daxxify means you may need fewer total visits over the year.","staff_close":"When a patient asks about reducing the frequency of their maintenance visits: ''Daxxify uses a peptide technology that helps it last about six months — so instead of coming in three or four times a year for your wrinkle relaxer, you may only need two visits. Vollure addresses the deeper lines around your nose and mouth, and it typically lasts about 18 months. So between the two, you''re getting longer-lasting results from both.''","staff_talking_points":"The key differentiator with Daxxify is duration. Vollure addresses the deeper lines around your nose and mouth caused by volume loss, not muscle movement. If patients ask how Daxxify is different from other neurotoxins: it uses the same botulinum toxin type A but with a peptide exchange technology that extends the duration and contains no human or animal byproducts. Note: Daxxify is a Revance product and Vollure is Allergan, so they don''t share a loyalty program. Focus on clinical fit, not brand bundling.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not guarantee the 6-month Daxxify duration — individual results vary and some patients may metabolize it faster.","Do not call this a ''liquid facelift'' or ''non-surgical facelift'' — these terms overclaim the outcome.","Do not state the combination is ''FDA approved'' as a combination — each product has its own individual FDA indication.","Do not reference Daxxify''s Revance ecosystem as a reason to avoid Allergan loyalty programs — focus on clinical fit."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Daxxify costs more than my usual neurotoxin. Is it worth it?","handling_language":"That''s a reasonable question. Daxxify''s longer duration — about six months — means fewer visits per year compared to a 3-4 month neurotoxin. Whether the per-visit cost difference works out in your favor depends on your situation. Your provider can help you look at your overall annual plan.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''it''s definitely worth it'' or make cost comparisons without knowing the patient''s specific plan."},{"objection_type":"do_I_need_both","patient_says":"Can''t Daxxify handle the nasolabial folds too?","handling_language":"Daxxify relaxes the muscles that create expression lines — it''s excellent for that. But the folds from your nose to the corners of your mouth are caused by volume loss in the tissue, not by muscle activity. No neurotoxin, regardless of duration, can restore that volume. Vollure addresses that specific concern through a different mechanism.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say Daxxify ''won''t work'' — it works for what it''s designed for. Frame the limitation clearly without dismissal."},{"objection_type":"fear_of_looking_overdone","patient_says":"I don''t want to look puffy or unnatural.","handling_language":"That''s a valid concern. Vollure is designed for the nasolabial fold area specifically — the goal is to soften those static lines by restoring natural volume at the right depth, not to add anything that looks artificial. The amount placed is carefully controlled.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the concern. Don''t say ''everyone does this now.''"},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"How much recovery time should I expect?","handling_language":"Both treatments have minimal downtime. There''s a possibility of temporary redness, minor swelling, or bruising at injection sites. Daxxify''s full effect is visible within 7-10 days. With filler, any minor swelling usually resolves within a few days. Your provider can advise based on your specific situation and any upcoming events.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''no downtime.'' Bruising and swelling are possible."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me think about adding Vollure — I''m not sure yet.","handling_language":"Of course. These are independent decisions — we can address the expression lines with Daxxify today and revisit the nasolabial folds at any future visit when you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t create urgency. Don''t reopen the conversation multiple times."}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin administered first in same-session protocols. If sequential: Daxxify 2 weeks before Vollure to assess muscle response before filling static NLF lines.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. If sequential: 2-week interval recommended. Maintenance scheduling advantage: Daxxify every ~6 months aligns efficiently with Vollure''s 12-18 month schedule.","downtime_note":"Minimal. Temporary redness, minor swelling, or bruising possible at injection sites for either or both treatments. Daxxify: effect visible within days, full at 7-10 days. Vollure: immediate volume with minor swelling resolving over days.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Daxxify every ~6 months (approximately 2 visits per year); Juvederm Vollure XC every 12-18 months. A Vollure touch-up can coincide with every second or third Daxxify visit, reducing total annual visits compared to traditional 3-4 month neurotoxin cycles.","rebooking_trigger":"At your 2-week Daxxify follow-up, we can assess the dynamic line response and discuss whether you''d like to address the nasolabial folds at that point or at a future visit.","next_visit_prompt":"If volume restoration in the nasolabial area is a goal, that conversation can happen when you''re ready — it doesn''t need to coincide with a Daxxify retreatment.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754: BoNT-A and HA fillers may be performed together in either sequence; combination is superior to either alone. Category-level evidence extrapolated to this cross-brand pair. FDA label — Daxxify: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; peptide exchange technology, ~6-month duration, no human/animal byproducts. FDA label — Juvederm Vollure XC: indicated for moderate to severe facial wrinkles and folds including nasolabial folds in adults over 21; VYCROSS crosslinking, 18-month duration. Accepted clinical practice: cross-ecosystem BoNT-A + HA filler combinations are standard; complementarity is mechanism-based.","evidence_level":"moderate","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    status  = 'draft'
WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
  AND content->>'pair_key' = 'daxxify__juvederm_vollure_xc';

-- Pair 21: Long-Lasting Smooth & Lift (daxxify__juvederm_voluma_xc)
-- Review status: PENDING
-- Tier: combination | Evidence: moderate
UPDATE agent_fuel_documents
SET
    content = '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"daxxify__juvederm_voluma_xc","patient_facing_name":"Long-Lasting Smooth & Lift","one_line_positioning":"Daxxify''s extended neuromodulation reduces annual visit frequency while Voluma restores the deep cheek structure that muscle relaxation cannot address.","package_goal":"Reduce expression lines and restore structural cheek volume with fewer annual visits","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients with dynamic upper-face wrinkles and age-related cheek volume loss who value longer intervals between neurotoxin retreatments.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or HA components. Very active patients should be counseled that Voluma may metabolize faster.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Cheek Volume Loss","Midface Aging","Facial Contour","Volume Loss"],"why_together":"Daxxify addresses movement-caused lines through neuromodulation with ~6-month duration; Voluma restores deep structural cheek volume through HA gel scaffold. They operate at different tissue layers — neuromuscular level vs deep supraperiosteal/subcutaneous level.","A_solves":"Daxxify relaxes the muscles creating dynamic expression lines (crow''s feet, frown lines, forehead) with extended duration reducing annual neurotoxin visits to approximately 2.","A_does_not_solve":"Daxxify cannot restore the structural volume lost in the cheeks or midface over time due to bone, fat pad, and collagen changes.","B_adds":"Voluma restores deep cheek volume and contour in the midface where structural loss creates a hollow, aged appearance — territory neurotoxin cannot address regardless of duration.","clinical_rationale":"Daxxify (~6-month duration via peptide exchange technology) combined with Voluma (up to 2-year duration via VYCROSS crosslinking) creates a long-duration treatment plan for both dynamic wrinkles and structural cheek volume loss. Daxxify reduces annual neurotoxin visits from 3-4 to approximately 2, and Voluma''s extended duration means cheek structure is maintained with infrequent touch-ups. Voluma is a structural filler injected deep in the cheeks — it is typically placed first in multi-filler protocols as the foundational scaffold. Category-level evidence supports BoNT-A + HA filler combinations (DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754); no product-specific study exists for this cross-brand pair. This is a cross-ecosystem pairing (Revance + Allergan). Patients who are highly active may metabolize Voluma faster.","patient_education_summary":"Daxxify is a longer-lasting wrinkle relaxer — it uses a unique peptide technology that helps it work for about six months, so you may need fewer maintenance visits compared to traditional options. Voluma is a structural filler designed specifically for the cheeks — it''s placed deep to restore the natural cheek volume that decreases with age, and it can last up to two years. If you''re noticing both expression lines and a loss of cheek fullness, these two products address different concerns through different mechanisms. Because both last longer than many alternatives, your overall maintenance schedule may be more manageable.","staff_close":"This pairing is worth understanding for patients who value longer-lasting results. When explaining: ''Daxxify relaxes expression lines and lasts about six months — so about two visits a year instead of three or four. Voluma restores cheek structure and can last up to two years. Together, these are two of the longer-duration options available, which means fewer maintenance visits overall.''","staff_talking_points":"On Voluma specifically: it''s a structural filler — placed deep, it acts as a foundation that can improve how the lower face looks by providing support from above. For highly active patients: Voluma may metabolize faster — set realistic duration expectations. Daxxify is Revance and Voluma is Allergan — different loyalty programs. Focus on the clinical fit and the efficiency benefit for the patient''s schedule.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not describe Voluma as ''lifting'' the cheeks in a way that implies a surgical lift — describe it as restoring structural volume and support.","Do not call this a ''liquid facelift'' — these terms overclaim and create unrealistic expectations.","Do not guarantee Daxxify''s 6-month duration — individual metabolism varies.","Do not guarantee Voluma duration for highly active patients — they may metabolize it faster."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Both at once seems like a lot — can I just do Daxxify for now?","handling_language":"Absolutely. These address two different things and can be done independently. Many patients start with the neurotoxin and decide about the cheek volume separately.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t imply they''re missing something by not doing both."},{"objection_type":"do_I_need_both","patient_says":"Will Daxxify make my cheeks look fuller?","handling_language":"Daxxify relaxes muscles, so it can soften the lines around your eyes and forehead. But the cheek area involves structural volume, not muscle movement — Daxxify wouldn''t change the cheek contour. Voluma addresses that specifically by restoring volume at the deep structural level.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss what Daxxify achieves. Be accurate that it doesn''t add volume."},{"objection_type":"fear_of_looking_overdone","patient_says":"I don''t want ''pillow face.''","handling_language":"That makes sense, and it''s exactly why Voluma is designed for deep cheek structure, not surface filling. The goal is to restore what was naturally there — appropriate volume at the right depth. The amount placed is carefully controlled.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the concern. Don''t say ''nobody will know.''"},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"I have an event coming up — is it safe to do both?","handling_language":"Good to know about the timing. Filler can cause minor swelling or bruising that takes a few days to settle. If the event is soon, you might consider doing Daxxify today and scheduling Voluma after. Your provider can help plan the timing.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''no downtime.'' Don''t dismiss the practical concern."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"I''m not sure about the filler part. Can I come back for that?","handling_language":"Of course. Voluma is an independent decision. We can address the expression lines today and revisit the cheek volume conversation at any future visit.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t create urgency. Don''t say ''prices may go up.''"}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin administered first in same-session protocols. If sequential: Daxxify 2 weeks before Voluma to assess muscle response. In multi-filler plans, Voluma (structural cheek volume) should be placed before fillers in lower facial zones.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. Both products have extended durations — Daxxify every ~6 months, Voluma every 18-24 months. A Voluma touch-up can typically coincide with a Daxxify retreatment visit.","downtime_note":"Minimal. Temporary redness, minor swelling, or bruising possible at injection sites. Daxxify: effect visible within days. Voluma: immediate volume with potential swelling at deep injection sites resolving over 1-2 weeks.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Daxxify every ~6 months (approximately 2 visits per year); Juvederm Voluma XC every 18-24 months. Both have extended durations — fewer total annual visits compared to traditional maintenance schedules. A Voluma touch-up can coincide with a Daxxify retreatment visit.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Daxxify follow-up, we can check how the dynamic lines have responded and discuss whether you''d like to address the cheek structure at that visit or schedule it separately.","next_visit_prompt":"If midface volume is a goal, we can discuss Voluma at your next visit or at a Daxxify retreatment appointment.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754: BoNT-A and HA fillers may be performed together in either sequence; combination superior to either alone. Category-level evidence extrapolated to this cross-brand pair. FDA label — Daxxify: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines; peptide exchange technology, ~6-month duration, no human/animal byproducts. FDA label — Juvederm Voluma XC: indicated for age-related volume deficit in the cheek area in adults over 21; VYCROSS crosslinking, up to 2-year duration. Accepted clinical practice: cross-ecosystem BoNT-A + HA filler combinations are standard.","evidence_level":"moderate","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    status  = 'draft'
WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
  AND content->>'pair_key' = 'daxxify__juvederm_voluma_xc';

-- Pair 22: Long-Lasting Smooth & Restore (Lyft) (daxxify__restylane_lyft)
-- Review status: PENDING
-- Tier: combination | Evidence: moderate
UPDATE agent_fuel_documents
SET
    content = '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"daxxify__restylane_lyft","patient_facing_name":"Long-Lasting Smooth & Restore (Lyft)","one_line_positioning":"Daxxify''s extended neuromodulation pairs with Restylane Lyft''s unique dual midface-and-hand indication to address aging concerns that neurotoxin cannot reach.","package_goal":"Reduce expression lines and restore midface or hand volume with a lower-visit maintenance schedule","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients with dynamic upper-face wrinkles and midface volume loss or hand volume loss seeking an efficient maintenance schedule. Relevant for patients with hand aging concerns alongside facial concerns.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients hypersensitive to gram-positive bacterial proteins (Restylane) or botulinum toxin. Patients seeking only one treatment modality.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Midface Volume Loss","Hand Volume Loss","Facial Aging"],"why_together":"Daxxify addresses movement-caused lines through neuromodulation; Restylane Lyft restores structural midface or hand volume through HA gel scaffold. The combination is mechanism-based — neuromodulation vs HA gel — not ecosystem-specific.","A_solves":"Daxxify relaxes the muscles causing expression lines with extended ~6-month duration, reducing annual neurotoxin visits to approximately 2.","A_does_not_solve":"Daxxify cannot restore lost volume in the midface or dorsal hands.","B_adds":"Restylane Lyft restores structural volume in the midface and has a unique dual FDA indication for both midface and dorsal hand augmentation — volume territory neurotoxin cannot address.","clinical_rationale":"Daxxify''s peptide exchange technology provides approximately 6-month duration with no human or animal byproducts, while Restylane Lyft''s NASHA-technology HA has a unique dual FDA indication for both midface volume and hands. Daxxify reduces annual neurotoxin visits from 3-4 to approximately 2, creating a more convenient maintenance schedule alongside Restylane Lyft''s 12-18 month duration. The hand volume indication for Restylane Lyft is unique among HA fillers — it addresses a concern that no neurotoxin can treat. Category-level evidence supports BoNT-A + HA filler combinations (DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754); no product-specific study exists for this cross-brand pair. This is a cross-ecosystem pairing (Revance + Galderma).","patient_education_summary":"Daxxify is a longer-lasting wrinkle relaxer that uses a unique peptide technology — it works for about six months for many patients, so you may need fewer visits for that portion of your treatment. Restylane Lyft is a filler with a unique distinction: it''s one of the few fillers approved for both midface volume and hands. If you''re noticing expression lines along with cheek hollowing or aging hands, these two treatments address completely different concerns. Daxxify handles the movement-based lines, while Restylane Lyft restores volume where it''s been lost — whether that''s in the cheeks, midface, or hands.","staff_close":"Two things to highlight with this combination. First, Daxxify''s duration: it helps it last about six months, so you''d come in about twice a year for the wrinkle relaxer instead of three or four times. Second, Restylane Lyft''s versatility: it''s one of the few fillers approved for both the midface and hands.","staff_talking_points":"On the hand indication: this is a genuine differentiator, not an add-on suggestion. Some patients seek hand treatment specifically — thinning skin, visible veins and tendons. Restylane Lyft is specifically indicated for that, which most fillers aren''t. Daxxify is Revance and Lyft is Galderma — different loyalty programs. Lead with clinical fit.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not guarantee Daxxify''s 6-month duration — individual metabolism varies.","Do not overstate the evidence — there is no product-specific published study for Daxxify + Restylane Lyft; the rationale is category-level.","Do not mention hand aging unprompted — only raise Lyft''s hand indication if the patient has expressed that concern.","Do not imply the cross-brand nature is a disadvantage — it is clinically irrelevant to the mechanism."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Daxxify today and think about filler later?","handling_language":"Of course. They address different things and can be done at completely separate visits. Many patients start with one and add the other when they''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t suggest the opportunity will pass. Don''t mention pricing pressure."},{"objection_type":"do_I_need_both","patient_says":"Will Daxxify help with the fullness in my cheeks?","handling_language":"Daxxify relaxes the muscles that cause expression lines — it''s excellent for that. The fullness or flatness in your cheeks is from structural volume changes, not from muscle activity. Daxxify can''t add volume. That''s what Restylane Lyft addresses through a different mechanism.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t be dismissive of what Daxxify achieves. Just clarify the mechanism difference."},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"I''m worried about bruising if I do both at once.","handling_language":"That''s a reasonable concern. With any injection there''s some chance of temporary bruising, and doing both in one visit involves more injection sites. Some patients prefer to space them out for that reason. We can schedule them a couple of weeks apart if you''d prefer.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''no bruising'' — bruising is possible. Don''t dismiss the practical concern."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"I''ll think about the filler — can we just do Daxxify today?","handling_language":"Absolutely. We''ll do Daxxify today, and if you decide later you''d like to discuss the filler, we can pick up that conversation at any time.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t create urgency. Don''t follow up with a hard close."}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin administered first in same-session protocols. If sequential: Daxxify 2 weeks before Restylane Lyft. If treating hands, timing is independent of facial neurotoxin — can be same session without interaction concern.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. If sequential: 2-week interval recommended. Daxxify every ~6 months; Restylane Lyft every 12-18 months depending on treatment area.","downtime_note":"Minimal. Temporary redness, minor swelling, or bruising at injection sites possible. Daxxify: effect visible within days. Restylane Lyft: immediate volume with potential minor swelling.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Daxxify every ~6 months (approximately 2 visits per year); Restylane Lyft every 12-18 months. The reduced Daxxify visit frequency means fewer overall appointments, and a Lyft touch-up can coincide with a Daxxify retreatment.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Daxxify follow-up, we can revisit the volume conversation. Restylane Lyft also has an FDA indication for hand rejuvenation if that becomes a concern at any point.","next_visit_prompt":"If you''d like to discuss midface volume or hand volume at your next visit, we can assess together.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754: BoNT-A and HA fillers may be performed together in either sequence; combination superior to either alone. Category-level evidence extrapolated to this cross-brand pair. FDA label — Daxxify: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines; peptide exchange technology, ~6-month duration, no human/animal byproducts. FDA label — Restylane Lyft: indicated for midface volume deficit and dorsal hand volume loss in adults over 21; NASHA technology; dual facial + hand indication unique among HA fillers. Accepted clinical practice: cross-ecosystem BoNT-A + HA filler combinations are standard.","evidence_level":"moderate","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    status  = 'draft'
WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
  AND content->>'pair_key' = 'daxxify__restylane_lyft';

-- Pair 23: Long-Lasting Smooth & Soften (Perioral) (daxxify__rha_redensity)
-- Review status: PENDING
-- Tier: combination | Evidence: moderate
UPDATE agent_fuel_documents
SET
    content = '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"daxxify__rha_redensity","patient_facing_name":"Long-Lasting Smooth & Soften (Perioral)","one_line_positioning":"Daxxify''s extended upper-face neuromodulation pairs with RHA Redensity''s resilient perioral HA to address two different facial zones through two different mechanisms — both from the Revance ecosystem.","package_goal":"Reduce upper-face expression lines and refine perioral fine lines with fewer annual neurotoxin visits","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients with dynamic upper-face wrinkles and perioral fine lines seeking a same-ecosystem combination; patients who value fewer annual neurotoxin appointments.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients with only one zone of concern, or patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or HA components.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Perioral Lines","Crow''s Feet","Lip Lines","Fine Lines"],"why_together":"Daxxify and RHA Redensity are both Revance products, creating ecosystem alignment. Daxxify addresses upper-face dynamic lines with extended duration; RHA Redensity''s resilient HA is designed specifically for perioral fine lines and dynamic areas around the mouth where neurotoxin is not appropriate.","A_solves":"Daxxify relaxes the muscles causing dynamic expression lines in the upper face — crow''s feet, forehead, frown lines — with ~6-month duration reducing annual visits.","A_does_not_solve":"Daxxify cannot address perioral fine lines; these require a filler designed for the high-mobility area around the mouth.","B_adds":"RHA Redensity uses resilient HA designed for the perioral zone''s constant movement, softening fine static lines around the lips that neurotoxin cannot treat.","clinical_rationale":"Daxxify and RHA Redensity are both Revance products, creating ecosystem alignment. Daxxify''s peptide exchange technology provides ~6-month duration for dynamic wrinkle relaxation, while RHA Redensity uses resilient HA designed specifically for perioral fine lines and dynamic facial areas. RHA Redensity is a finishing filler that refines fine lines in areas of constant movement (lips, perioral region) where traditional fillers may not perform as well. The combination addresses upper-face dynamic wrinkles (Daxxify, with fewer annual visits) alongside perioral fine line refinement (RHA Redensity). Same ecosystem means loyalty program alignment for patients. Category-level evidence supports BoNT-A + HA filler combinations (DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754); no product-specific study exists for this pair.","patient_education_summary":"Daxxify is a longer-lasting wrinkle relaxer — it uses a unique peptide technology that works for about six months for many patients, meaning fewer maintenance visits for expression lines like forehead wrinkles and crow''s feet. The fine lines around your mouth are a different concern — they''re in an area that moves constantly with talking, eating, and smiling. RHA Redensity is a specialized filler designed for exactly those delicate lines. It uses a resilient formula that flexes with your natural expressions rather than stiffening the area. Both products are made by the same company, Revance, and they address two different concerns through two different approaches.","staff_close":"This is a same-ecosystem pairing — both Daxxify and RHA Redensity are Revance products, so patients can benefit from a single loyalty program. When explaining: ''Daxxify addresses your expression lines and lasts about six months, so fewer visits per year. RHA Redensity is a specialized filler for the fine lines around your mouth — it''s designed to move with your expressions rather than resist them.''","staff_talking_points":"On RHA Redensity''s role: think of it as a finishing treatment. If a patient has had their expression lines treated with Daxxify, RHA Redensity refines those remaining perioral lines that other treatments can''t fully address. The Revance ecosystem alignment is a genuine convenience factor for patients — single loyalty program — not just a sales angle. For cross-ecosystem alternatives, staff should note that other neurotoxins can pair with RHA Redensity but won''t share the loyalty benefit.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not suggest Daxxify or any neurotoxin around the mouth — perioral neurotoxin can impair speech, eating, and facial function.","Do not imply RHA Redensity adds volume to the lips — it treats perioral rhytids, not lip augmentation.","Do not overstate perioral maintenance duration — RHA Redensity may require more frequent retreatment than other anatomical zones.","Do not guarantee Daxxify''s 6-month duration — individual metabolism varies."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"I only wanted Daxxify today — can we talk about the perioral lines another time?","handling_language":"Of course. These are completely independent treatments. We can address the upper face today and revisit the perioral concern whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t suggest urgency. Don''t bundle a hard close."},{"objection_type":"do_I_need_both","patient_says":"Can''t Daxxify treat the lines around my mouth too?","handling_language":"The lines around the eyes and forehead are caused by muscle movement — that''s exactly what Daxxify addresses. But the fine lines around your mouth are in a high-mobility zone where a flexible filler that moves with your expressions works better. Applying neurotoxin to the perioral area could actually affect normal lip and mouth function.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say Daxxify ''doesn''t work'' around the mouth. Clarify it''s about zone-appropriate treatment."},{"objection_type":"fear_of_looking_overdone","patient_says":"I don''t want my lips to look done.","handling_language":"RHA Redensity isn''t a lip augmentation — it''s designed to treat the fine lines around the lips, not to add volume to the lips themselves. The goal is to soften those small lines while preserving natural lip shape.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the concern. Clarify the distinction between perioral line treatment and lip augmentation."},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"The perioral area bruises easily — how much time should I plan for?","handling_language":"The perioral area does tend to bruise more easily for some patients. If you have an event coming up, scheduling Daxxify today and the perioral filler a few weeks after the event is a practical approach.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the concern. Don''t say ''no bruising.''"},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me think about the perioral filler.","handling_language":"No rush at all. These are independent decisions. We''ll do whatever you''re comfortable with today and keep the conversation open.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t push. Don''t reopen the sales conversation immediately."}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin administered first in same-session protocols. If sequential: Daxxify 2 weeks before RHA Redensity to assess upper-face muscle response. RHA Redensity is typically a finishing step after structural fillers if any are being placed.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. If sequential: 2-week interval recommended. Daxxify every ~6 months; RHA Redensity perioral every 6-12 months (shorter window due to high mobility).","downtime_note":"Daxxify: effect visible within days, minimal visible downtime. RHA Redensity perioral: possible bruising and swelling; perioral area is particularly prone to bruising. Plan accordingly before events.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Daxxify every ~6 months (approximately 2 visits per year); RHA Redensity perioral every 6-12 months. Both are Revance products, enabling single-program loyalty tracking. The perioral maintenance window is shorter than most HA fillers due to high mobility.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Daxxify follow-up, if you''d like to address the perioral lines, that''s a natural time to revisit the RHA Redensity conversation.","next_visit_prompt":"If perioral fine lines remain a concern after seeing your Daxxify results, we can discuss RHA Redensity at your next visit.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754: BoNT-A and HA fillers may be performed together in either sequence; combination superior to either alone. Category-level evidence extrapolated to this pair. FDA label — Daxxify: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines; peptide exchange technology, ~6-month duration, no human/animal byproducts. FDA label — RHA Redensity: indicated for perioral area (superficial to mid dermis) for correction of dynamic perioral rhytids in adults over 22; resilient HA for dynamic facial areas. Accepted clinical practice: zone-based complementarity (upper-face neurotoxin + perioral filler) is standard in comprehensive facial rejuvenation protocols.","evidence_level":"moderate","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    status  = 'draft'
WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
  AND content->>'pair_key' = 'daxxify__rha_redensity';

-- Pair 24: Broad Smooth & Restore (dysport__juvederm_vollure_xc)
-- Review status: PENDING
-- Tier: combination | Evidence: moderate
UPDATE agent_fuel_documents
SET
    content = '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"dysport__juvederm_vollure_xc","patient_facing_name":"Broad Smooth & Restore","one_line_positioning":"Dysport''s broad-diffusion pattern addresses large dynamic zones while Vollure softens the static nasolabial fold lines that neurotoxin cannot correct.","package_goal":"Reduce dynamic wrinkles across broad facial zones and soften nasolabial folds","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients with both dynamic upper-face wrinkles (especially forehead and crow''s feet) and moderate-to-severe static nasolabial folds.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or HA components. Patients seeking only one treatment modality.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Nasolabial Folds","Volume Loss","Fine Lines","Facial Aging"],"why_together":"Dysport addresses movement-caused lines in broad facial zones through neuromodulation; Vollure restores mid-depth volume in the nasolabial folds that muscle relaxation cannot correct. Different mechanisms at different tissue layers.","A_solves":"Dysport relaxes the muscles causing dynamic expression lines, with broader diffusion that makes it well-suited for large treatment zones like the forehead and lateral crow''s feet. Faster onset at 2-5 days.","A_does_not_solve":"Dysport cannot restore volume or soften lines that remain at rest.","B_adds":"Vollure restores mid-depth volume in the nasolabial folds and moderate facial lines that persist at rest — static lines that neurotoxin cannot treat.","clinical_rationale":"Dysport''s broader diffusion pattern makes it well-suited for treating large dynamic zones (forehead, lateral crow''s feet) with fewer injection points, while Vollure''s VYCROSS-crosslinked HA addresses nasolabial folds and moderate facial lines with an 18-month duration. The combination treats two distinct layers of facial aging: Dysport relaxes muscles causing expression lines (with faster onset at 2-5 days vs 7-14 for some neurotoxins), while Vollure restores mid-depth volume loss in the lower face. Category-level evidence supports BoNT-A + HA filler combinations (DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754); no product-specific study exists for this cross-brand pair. Dysport maintenance: every 3-4 months. Vollure maintenance: every 12-18 months.","patient_education_summary":"Dysport works by relaxing the muscles that create expression lines — it''s especially effective for smoothing broad areas like the forehead and crow''s feet, and many patients notice results within a few days. But Dysport can''t address the deeper lines around your nose and mouth that come from volume loss over time. Vollure is a hyaluronic acid filler designed specifically for those nasolabial fold lines, and it typically lasts about 18 months. If you''re seeing both expression lines and those deeper smile lines, addressing them together often produces a more balanced result than treating either one alone.","staff_close":"When a patient mentions both forehead lines and nasolabial folds: ''Those are actually two different concerns with two different causes. The forehead and crow''s feet lines come from muscle movement — Dysport is designed for those areas and tends to work well across broader zones. The deeper lines around your nose and mouth are from volume loss — that''s where Vollure comes in. Vollure is specifically designed for those nasolabial fold lines.''","staff_talking_points":"Dysport''s key differentiator is its broader diffusion pattern and faster onset (2-5 days). This helps patients with large treatment zones like the forehead see results sooner. Vollure addresses a different concern entirely — the deeper, static NLF lines caused by volume loss. Some patients choose to address both in the same visit, others prefer to start with one and see how they feel. There''s no medical reason they can''t be done at the same time.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not call this a ''liquid facelift'' or ''non-surgical facelift'' — these terms overclaim the outcome.","Do not describe Dysport''s broader diffusion as superior to other neurotoxins — it is a characteristic suited to certain treatment zones, not a universal advantage.","Do not state the combination is ''FDA approved'' as a combination — each product has its own FDA indication.","Do not overpromise on evidence — there is no product-specific published study for Dysport + Vollure; the rationale is category-level."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Dysport today and think about filler later?","handling_language":"Of course. Dysport and filler address different things — you can do either independently. Many patients start with the neurotoxin and add filler at a later visit when they''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t suggest the opportunity will pass."},{"objection_type":"do_I_need_both","patient_says":"Can''t Dysport take care of the nasolabial folds?","handling_language":"Dysport is excellent for expression lines caused by muscle movement — forehead, crow''s feet, frown lines. But the nasolabial folds are caused by volume loss in the tissue, not muscle activity. No neurotoxin can restore that volume. Vollure addresses that specific concern through a different approach.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss Dysport''s efficacy. Frame the NLF limitation as mechanism-specific, not a product limitation."},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"I have plans this weekend — how much bruising should I expect?","handling_language":"With any injection there''s a possibility of minor bruising or swelling. Doing both in one visit means more injection sites. If you''d prefer to minimize risk ahead of weekend plans, spacing them out by a couple of weeks is a reasonable approach.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''no bruising.'' Don''t minimize the practical concern."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me start with Dysport and revisit the filler next time.","handling_language":"That''s a very common approach. We can do the Dysport today and keep the NLF conversation open for your next visit.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t reopen the close. Don''t create urgency."}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin administered first in same-session protocols. If sequential: Dysport 2 weeks before Vollure to assess muscle response. Dysport''s faster onset (2-5 days) allows earlier assessment of dynamic wrinkle improvement.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. If sequential: 2-week interval recommended. Dysport every 3-4 months; Vollure every 12-18 months.","downtime_note":"Minimal. Temporary redness, minor swelling, or bruising possible at injection sites. Dysport: effect visible within 2-5 days. Vollure: immediate volume with minor swelling resolving over days.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Dysport every 3-4 months; Juvederm Vollure XC every 12-18 months. Patients typically schedule neurotoxin visits more frequently. Many align one annual Vollure visit with the start of a Dysport cycle.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Dysport follow-up, we can assess how the dynamic lines have responded. If you''d like to address the nasolabial folds, that conversation can happen then or at any future visit.","next_visit_prompt":"If volume restoration in the NLF area is a goal, we can discuss Vollure at your next visit.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754: BoNT-A and HA fillers may be performed together in either sequence; combination superior to either alone. Category-level evidence extrapolated to this cross-brand pair. FDA label — Dysport: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; broader diffusion pattern, faster onset 2-5 days. FDA label — Juvederm Vollure XC: indicated for moderate to severe facial wrinkles and folds including nasolabial folds in adults over 21; VYCROSS crosslinking, 18-month duration. Accepted clinical practice: BoNT-A + HA filler combinations are standard; complementarity is mechanism-based.","evidence_level":"moderate","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    status  = 'draft'
WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
  AND content->>'pair_key' = 'dysport__juvederm_vollure_xc';

-- Pair 25: Broad Smooth & Lift (dysport__juvederm_voluma_xc)
-- Review status: PENDING
-- Tier: combination | Evidence: moderate
UPDATE agent_fuel_documents
SET
    content = '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"dysport__juvederm_voluma_xc","patient_facing_name":"Broad Smooth & Lift","one_line_positioning":"Dysport''s broad-coverage neuromodulation addresses large dynamic zones while Voluma rebuilds the deep cheek foundation that relaxing muscles cannot restore.","package_goal":"Reduce dynamic wrinkles across broad facial zones and restore structural cheek volume","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients with dynamic upper-face wrinkles and age-related cheek volume loss creating a hollow or descended midface appearance.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients seeking only one treatment modality, or patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or HA components. Very active patients should expect variable Voluma duration.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Cheek Volume Loss","Midface Aging","Facial Contour","Volume Loss"],"why_together":"Dysport addresses movement-caused lines through neuromodulation with broader diffusion; Voluma restores deep structural volume in the cheek area through HA gel scaffold. They work at different tissue layers — neuromuscular level vs deep supraperiosteal/subcutaneous level.","A_solves":"Dysport relaxes the muscles causing upper-face expression lines, with broader diffusion suited for forehead and crow''s feet treatment zones. Faster onset at 2-5 days.","A_does_not_solve":"Dysport cannot restore the structural volume lost in the cheeks or midface.","B_adds":"Voluma restores deep cheek volume and contour where structural loss creates a hollow, aged appearance — territory that neuromodulation cannot address.","clinical_rationale":"Dysport''s broader diffusion pattern treats large dynamic zones (forehead, crow''s feet) effectively with fewer injection points, while Voluma provides deep structural volume restoration in the cheeks using VYCROSS technology with up to 2-year duration. This combination addresses two distinct layers: Dysport relaxes the muscles causing upper-face expression lines (with faster onset at 2-5 days), while Voluma rebuilds the foundational cheek structure lost with aging. Voluma is typically placed first in multi-filler protocols as a structural base. Category-level evidence supports BoNT-A + HA filler combinations (DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754). Patients who are highly active may metabolize Voluma faster. Dysport maintenance: every 3-4 months. Voluma maintenance: every 18-24 months.","patient_education_summary":"Dysport is designed to relax the muscles that cause expression lines — it works especially well across broader areas like the forehead and around the eyes, and you may notice results within just a few days. But relaxing those muscles can''t bring back the cheek volume that naturally decreases over time. Voluma is a structural filler placed deep in the cheeks to restore that foundation — it''s one of the longer-lasting fillers available, often holding for up to two years. If you''re noticing both expression lines up top and a loss of cheek fullness, treating both addresses the full picture of facial aging rather than just one part of it.","staff_close":"When a patient says they look tired or their face looks deflated, help them separate the concerns: ''The lines on your forehead and around your eyes are from muscle movement — Dysport addresses those by relaxing the muscles. But if you''re also noticing your cheeks look flatter than they used to, that''s structural volume loss. Voluma is designed specifically for deep cheek volume — it acts like a scaffold to restore that structure.''","staff_talking_points":"Dysport''s broader diffusion is a clinical characteristic — useful for large treatment zones, not universally superior. On Voluma: it''s a structural filler that provides a cheek foundation, which can improve the appearance of the lower face by providing support from above. For highly active patients: set realistic Voluma duration expectations. Voluma is placed first in multi-filler protocols if other fillers are also being considered.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not describe Voluma as ''lifting'' the cheeks in a way that implies a surgical lift — describe it as restoring structural volume and support.","Do not call this a ''liquid facelift'' — overclaims and creates unrealistic expectations.","Do not guarantee Voluma duration for highly active patients.","Do not describe Dysport''s diffusion as an advantage over other neurotoxins without context — it is zone-specific, not universally superior."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I start with just Dysport today?","handling_language":"Absolutely. These address two different concerns — you can do either independently and add the other whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t imply they''re missing something by not doing both."},{"objection_type":"do_I_need_both","patient_says":"Will Dysport help with the hollowness in my cheeks?","handling_language":"Dysport relaxes the muscles that cause expression lines — that''s what it does. The hollowness in the cheeks is from structural volume loss, which is a completely different process. Dysport doesn''t add volume. Voluma specifically addresses that by restoring the deep cheek structure.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss Dysport''s value. Clarify the structural vs. movement distinction."},{"objection_type":"fear_of_looking_overdone","patient_says":"I''m afraid of looking puffy.","handling_language":"That makes sense. Voluma is a structural filler — it''s placed deep to rebuild what was there naturally, not to add bulk on the surface. The amount placed is carefully controlled, and the goal is a result that looks like you at a better moment in time.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss the concern. Don''t say ''nobody will notice.''"},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"I''m worried about doing both at once before an event.","handling_language":"Good to be thinking about timing. Filler can cause minor swelling or bruising that takes a few days to settle. If an event is soon, you might consider doing Dysport today and scheduling Voluma after the event.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''no downtime.'' Don''t dismiss the practical concern."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"I want to think about the filler — can we just do Dysport?","handling_language":"Of course. We''ll do Dysport today and the Voluma conversation stays open for whenever you''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t create urgency. Don''t follow up with pressure."}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin administered first in same-session protocols. If sequential: Dysport 2 weeks before Voluma. Dysport''s faster onset (2-5 days) allows earlier assessment of dynamic wrinkle improvement. In multi-filler plans, Voluma placed first to provide cheek scaffold.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. If sequential: 2-week interval recommended. Dysport every 3-4 months; Voluma every 18-24 months.","downtime_note":"Minimal. Temporary redness, minor swelling, or bruising possible. Dysport: effect visible within 2-5 days. Voluma: immediate volume with potential swelling at deep injection sites, resolving over 1-2 weeks.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Dysport every 3-4 months; Juvederm Voluma XC every 18-24 months. Less-frequent Voluma maintenance means patients can align filler touchups with less disruption to their regular Dysport schedule. Neuromodulation may preserve Voluma longevity by reducing mechanical stress.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Dysport follow-up, we can check how the dynamic lines have responded and discuss whether you''d like to address cheek structure at that visit or schedule separately.","next_visit_prompt":"If midface volume is a goal, we can discuss Voluma at any future visit — it doesn''t need to align with a Dysport appointment.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754: BoNT-A and HA fillers may be performed together in either sequence; combination superior to either alone. Category-level evidence. FDA label — Dysport: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; broader diffusion, faster onset 2-5 days. FDA label — Juvederm Voluma XC: indicated for age-related volume deficit in the cheek area in adults over 21; VYCROSS crosslinking, up to 2-year duration. Accepted clinical practice: BoNT-A + HA filler combinations are standard; neuromodulation may preserve filler longevity.","evidence_level":"moderate","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    status  = 'draft'
WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
  AND content->>'pair_key' = 'dysport__juvederm_voluma_xc';

