SET
    content = '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"dysport__restylane_lyft","patient_facing_name":"Broad Smooth & Restore (Galderma)","one_line_positioning":"Dysport and Restylane Lyft are both Galderma products that address complementary concerns — expression lines and structural volume — through completely different mechanisms.","package_goal":"Reduce dynamic wrinkles in broad facial zones and restore midface or hand volume","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients with dynamic upper-face wrinkles and midface volume loss or hand volume loss, particularly those interested in staying within the Galderma product ecosystem.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients hypersensitive to gram-positive bacterial proteins (Restylane) or botulinum toxin. Patients seeking only one treatment modality.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Midface Volume Loss","Hand Volume Loss","Facial Aging"],"why_together":"Dysport and Restylane Lyft are both Galderma products, creating ecosystem alignment. Dysport addresses movement-caused lines through neuromodulation; Restylane Lyft restores structural midface or hand volume through HA gel scaffold. The complementarity is mechanism-based.","A_solves":"Dysport relaxes the muscles causing expression lines with broader diffusion suited for forehead and crow''s feet. Faster onset at 2-5 days.","A_does_not_solve":"Dysport cannot restore lost volume in the midface or hands.","B_adds":"Restylane Lyft restores structural volume in the midface and has a unique dual FDA indication for both midface and dorsal hand augmentation — unique among HA fillers.","clinical_rationale":"Dysport and Restylane Lyft are both Galderma products, creating ecosystem alignment for practices. Dysport''s broader diffusion pattern treats large dynamic zones effectively with fewer injection points, while Restylane Lyft is a NASHA-technology HA filler with a unique dual FDA indication for both midface volume and hands. This combination addresses dynamic expression lines (Dysport, faster onset at 2-5 days) alongside structural volume loss in the midface or age-related hand volume loss. Restylane Lyft''s hand indication is unique among HA fillers. Category-level evidence supports BoNT-A + HA filler combinations (DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754). Dysport maintenance: every 3-4 months. Restylane Lyft maintenance: every 12-18 months.","patient_education_summary":"Dysport relaxes the muscles that create expression lines like forehead wrinkles and crow''s feet — it''s designed to work well across broad areas and you may see results within a few days. But Dysport can''t address volume loss in your cheeks or hands. Restylane Lyft is a filler that''s specifically approved for restoring midface volume, and it''s one of the few fillers also approved for hands. If you''re noticing expression lines along with cheek hollowing or aging hands, these two treatments address different aspects of the aging process. They''re made by the same company and work through completely different mechanisms.","staff_close":"Dysport and Restylane Lyft are both Galderma products, so if a patient asks about brand consistency or loyalty programs, you can mention they''re from the same family. When explaining the pairing: ''Dysport works on the muscles that cause expression lines. Restylane Lyft addresses volume loss, and it''s unique because it''s approved for both midface volume and hands.''","staff_talking_points":"On the hand indication: this is a genuine differentiator — no other HA filler has the dual face-and-hands FDA approval. Help patients understand the distinct roles without implying they need both. The Galderma ecosystem alignment is a genuine convenience factor — single loyalty program, aligned training. Focus on clinical fit first, ecosystem second.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not use the Galderma ecosystem alignment as a primary reason to choose this combination — clinical fit is the primary reason.","Do not mention hand aging unprompted — only raise Lyft''s hand indication if the patient has expressed that concern.","Do not overstate evidence — there is no product-specific published study for Dysport + Restylane Lyft; the rationale is category-level.","Do not describe Dysport''s diffusion as superior to other neurotoxins without zone-specific context."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Dysport today and think about filler later?","handling_language":"Absolutely. These are completely independent treatments addressing different concerns. You can start with Dysport and revisit the volume conversation at any future visit.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t suggest urgency or that they''re missing an opportunity."},{"objection_type":"do_I_need_both","patient_says":"Will Dysport help with my cheek hollowing?","handling_language":"Dysport is excellent for expression lines — forehead, crow''s feet, frown lines. But cheek hollowing is from structural volume loss, which is a different process entirely. Dysport doesn''t add volume. Restylane Lyft specifically addresses that by restoring the structure.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss Dysport''s value. Clearly distinguish movement from volume loss."},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"I''m worried about bruising if I do both at once.","handling_language":"That''s reasonable. With any injection there''s some chance of temporary bruising, and doing both in one visit involves more sites. Some patients prefer to space them out for that reason. We can schedule them a couple weeks apart.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''no bruising.'' Don''t dismiss the practical concern."},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"I''ll think about adding the filler. Can we do Dysport today?","handling_language":"Of course. We''ll do the Dysport today and the filler conversation stays open for any future visit.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t create urgency. Don''t reopen the close."}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin administered first in same-session protocols. If sequential: Dysport 2 weeks before Restylane Lyft. If treating hands, timing is independent of facial neurotoxin — can be same session.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. If sequential: 2-week interval recommended. Dysport every 3-4 months; Restylane Lyft every 12-18 months depending on treatment area.","downtime_note":"Minimal. Temporary redness, minor swelling, or bruising possible. Dysport: effect visible within 2-5 days. Restylane Lyft: immediate volume with potential minor swelling.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Dysport every 3-4 months; Restylane Lyft every 12-18 months. Both are Galderma products — single loyalty program. Lyft touch-ups can be coordinated with Dysport appointments for convenience.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Dysport follow-up, we can revisit the volume conversation. Restylane Lyft also has an FDA indication for hand rejuvenation if that becomes a concern.","next_visit_prompt":"If midface or hand volume is a goal, we can discuss Restylane Lyft at your next visit.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754: BoNT-A and HA fillers may be performed together in either sequence; combination superior to either alone. Category-level evidence. FDA label — Dysport: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines; broader diffusion, faster onset 2-5 days. FDA label — Restylane Lyft: indicated for midface volume deficit and dorsal hand volume loss in adults over 21; NASHA technology; dual facial + hand indication unique among HA fillers. Galderma ecosystem: both products share manufacturer alignment, training programs, and loyalty platform.","evidence_level":"moderate","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    status  = 'draft'
