SELECT
    'pairing_fuel',
    'draft',
    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"jeuveau__juvederm_vollure_xc","patient_facing_name":"Smooth & Restore (Jeuveau)","one_line_positioning":"Jeuveau''s aesthetics-only neuromodulation addresses dynamic expression lines while Vollure corrects the nasolabial fold volume loss that no neurotoxin can restore.","package_goal":"Reduce expression lines and soften nasolabial folds","ideal_candidate":"Adult patients with dynamic upper-face wrinkles and moderate-to-severe static nasolabial folds; patients whose practice uses Jeuveau as their standard neurotoxin.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients hypersensitive to botulinum toxin or HA components. Patients seeking only one treatment modality.","concern_tags":["Dynamic Wrinkles","Nasolabial Folds","Volume Loss","Fine Lines","Facial Aging"],"why_together":"Jeuveau addresses movement-caused lines through neuromodulation; Vollure restores mid-depth volume in the nasolabial folds that muscle relaxation cannot correct. The complementarity is mechanism-based — neuromodulation vs HA gel scaffold at different tissue layers.","A_solves":"Jeuveau relaxes the muscles that create dynamic expression lines (frown lines, crow''s feet, forehead) — it is an aesthetics-only neurotoxin designed specifically for cosmetic use.","A_does_not_solve":"Jeuveau cannot restore lost volume or soften lines that remain at rest when the face is relaxed.","B_adds":"Vollure restores mid-depth volume in the nasolabial folds and moderate facial lines that persist at rest — static volume loss that neurotoxin cannot address.","clinical_rationale":"Jeuveau (''Newtox'') is an aesthetics-only neurotoxin manufactured using Hi-Pure technology by Evolus — it has no therapeutic indications, being designed solely for cosmetic use. It addresses dynamic wrinkles through the botulinum toxin type A mechanism. Vollure''s VYCROSS-crosslinked HA addresses nasolabial folds and moderate facial lines with an 18-month duration. The combination treats dynamic expression lines (Jeuveau) alongside mid-depth volume loss in the NLF area (Vollure). Note: Jeuveau has limited product-specific published evidence compared to longer-established neurotoxins. The neurotoxin + filler complementarity is mechanism-based and well-established at the category level (DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754). This is a cross-ecosystem pairing (Evolus + Allergan). Jeuveau maintenance: every 3-4 months. Vollure maintenance: every 12-18 months.","patient_education_summary":"Jeuveau is a wrinkle relaxer designed specifically for cosmetic use — it works by relaxing the muscles that cause expression lines like frown lines and crow''s feet. But it can''t address the deeper lines that run from your nose to your mouth — those nasolabial folds come from volume loss over time, not muscle movement. Vollure is a filler designed specifically for those lines, and it typically lasts about 18 months. If you''re noticing both expression lines and those deeper smile-line folds, addressing both treats the full picture — movement-based lines and volume-based lines are two different concerns that each need their own approach.","staff_close":"When explaining Jeuveau to patients: ''Jeuveau is sometimes called Newtox — it''s a wrinkle relaxer made specifically for cosmetic use. It works to relax the muscles that cause expression lines.'' On the Vollure pairing: ''Vollure addresses a different concern — the deeper lines around your nose and mouth that come from volume loss, not muscle movement. It''s specifically designed for nasolabial folds and tends to last about 18 months.''","staff_talking_points":"If patients ask how Jeuveau compares to other neurotoxins: be straightforward that it works through the same mechanism, and the provider can discuss which option makes the most sense. Jeuveau is an Evolus product and Vollure is Allergan — different loyalty programs. Let the clinical discussion guide product selection, not the brand ecosystem.","do_not_say":{"universal":["Unsupported clinical claims (e.g., ''clinically proven to reverse aging'')","Guarantees (e.g., ''I guarantee you''ll love the results'')","''You need this'' pressure (e.g., ''You really need both'')","Fear-based selling (e.g., ''Without this, your skin will only get worse'')","Competitor disparagement","''Liquid facelift'' overclaims","''No downtime'' when downtime exists","Permanent result claims","Off-label combination approval claims","''No risk'' statements","Price/value claims practices may not honor","Before/after exaggerations (e.g., ''20 years younger'')"],"pair_specific":["Do not overstate Jeuveau''s evidence base — it has limited product-specific published studies compared to longer-established neurotoxins.","Do not call this a ''liquid facelift'' — overclaims the outcome.","Do not compare Jeuveau to other neurotoxins in ways that disparage competitors.","Do not state the combination is ''FDA approved'' as a combination — each product has its own indication."],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Can I just do Jeuveau today and think about filler later?","handling_language":"Of course. These address different things and can be done at separate visits. Many patients start with the neurotoxin and add filler whenever they''re ready.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t suggest urgency."},{"objection_type":"do_I_need_both","patient_says":"Can''t Jeuveau handle the nasolabial folds?","handling_language":"Jeuveau is excellent for expression lines caused by muscle movement — frown lines, crow''s feet. But the nasolabial folds are caused by volume loss in the tissue, not by muscle activity. No neurotoxin can restore that volume. Vollure addresses that specific concern through a different mechanism.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t dismiss Jeuveau. Clearly distinguish the mechanism limitation."},{"objection_type":"newtox_question","patient_says":"What''s different about Jeuveau compared to Botox?","handling_language":"Jeuveau is an aesthetics-only neurotoxin made by Evolus — it works through the same mechanism as other neurotoxins by relaxing the muscles that cause expression lines. Your provider can walk you through which option makes the most sense for your individual case.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t disparage other neurotoxins. Don''t make unsupported efficacy comparisons."},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"How much recovery should I plan for?","handling_language":"Both have minimal downtime. There''s a possibility of temporary redness or minor bruising at injection sites. With filler, any minor swelling usually resolves within a few days. Your provider can advise based on your upcoming schedule.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t say ''no downtime.''"},{"objection_type":"I_will_think_about_it","patient_says":"Let me think about the filler part.","handling_language":"No rush. These are independent decisions. We can do Jeuveau today and revisit the Vollure conversation at any future visit.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t create urgency."}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin administered first in same-session protocols. If sequential: Jeuveau 2 weeks before Vollure to assess muscle response before addressing static NLF lines.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. If sequential: 2-week interval recommended. Jeuveau every 3-4 months; Vollure every 12-18 months.","downtime_note":"Minimal. Temporary redness, minor swelling, or bruising possible at injection sites. Jeuveau: effect develops over 7-14 days. Vollure: immediate volume with minor swelling resolving over days.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Jeuveau every 3-4 months; Juvederm Vollure XC every 12-18 months. Patients typically schedule neurotoxin more frequently, with Vollure aligned to natural renewal intervals.","rebooking_trigger":"At your Jeuveau follow-up, we can assess the dynamic line response and discuss whether you''d like to address the nasolabial folds at that visit or in the future.","next_visit_prompt":"If NLF softening is a goal, we can discuss Vollure at any future visit when you''re ready.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754: BoNT-A and HA fillers may be performed together in either sequence; combination superior to either alone. Category-level evidence extrapolated to this pair; Jeuveau has limited product-specific published evidence. FDA label — Jeuveau: indicated for moderate to severe glabellar lines in adults; aesthetics-only indication, Hi-Pure manufacturing technology. FDA label — Juvederm Vollure XC: indicated for moderate to severe facial wrinkles and folds including nasolabial folds in adults over 21; VYCROSS crosslinking, 18-month duration. Accepted clinical practice: BoNT-A + HA filler combinations are standard; mechanism-based complementarity applies.","evidence_level":"moderate","review_status":"draft","audience":["agent","staff"],"patient_safe":false,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
    NOW(),
    NOW()
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM agent_fuel_documents
    WHERE fuel_type = 'pairing_fuel'
      AND content->>'pair_key' = 'jeuveau__juvederm_vollure_xc'
