    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"jeuveau__restylane_lyft","product_a":"Jeuveau","product_b":"Restylane Lyft","patient_facing_name":"Relax & Lift","one_line_positioning":"Jeuveau relaxes expression lines while Restylane Lyft restores midface volume and can address aging hands — the only HA filler approved for both.","package_goal":"Treat dynamic wrinkles and midface or hand volume loss together","ideal_candidate":"Patient experiencing upper-face expression lines alongside midface volume loss or visibly aging hands (thinning skin, visible tendons and veins); patient seeking comprehensive age-related improvement across face and/or hands.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patient with single isolated concern; patients with neurotoxin or HA contraindications; highly active patients should have realistic duration expectations.","concern_tags":["dynamic wrinkles","frown lines","crow''s feet","cheek volume loss","midface aging","hand aging","facial aging"],"why_together":"Jeuveau relaxes upper-face expression muscles; Restylane Lyft restores midface volume or hand volume. Different tissue layers, different aging mechanisms — and uniquely, Lyft''s dual indication means it can address aging in both the face and hands in the same appointment.","A_solves":"Relaxes muscles causing dynamic expression lines (frown lines, crow''s feet, forehead lines)","A_does_not_solve":"Cannot restore lost midface or hand volume","B_adds":"Immediate HA volume restoration in midface (NASHA technology); FDA-approved for dorsal hands — unique dual indication among HA fillers","clinical_rationale":"Jeuveau (prabotulinumtoxinA-xvfs) is an aesthetics-only neurotoxin with Hi-Pure technology, addressing dynamic wrinkles through the standard BoNT-A mechanism. Restylane Lyft uses NASHA technology and has a unique dual FDA indication for both midface volume and hands — the hand indication is unique among HA fillers. The combination addresses expression lines (Jeuveau) alongside midface volume loss or hand aging (Restylane Lyft). Jeuveau has limited product-specific published evidence compared to longer-established neurotoxins. This is a cross-ecosystem pairing (Evolus + Galderma). Jeuveau maintenance: every 3-4 months. Restylane Lyft maintenance: every 12-18 months depending on treatment area.","patient_education_summary":"Jeuveau is a wrinkle relaxer made specifically for cosmetic use — it relaxes the muscles causing expression lines like frown lines and crow''s feet. But it can''t address volume loss in your cheeks or hands. Restylane Lyft is a filler with a unique distinction: it''s one of the few fillers approved for both midface volume and hands. If you''re concerned about aging hands — where the skin thins and veins become more visible — Lyft is specifically designed for that. And if you''re also noticing cheek hollowing, it addresses that too. These are different concerns requiring different treatments.","staff_close":"Lyft is one of the only fillers approved for both the midface and hands — if a patient mentions their hands as a concern, this is specifically indicated for that.","staff_talking_points":"When explaining this combination: ''Jeuveau handles the expression lines — forehead, frown lines, crow''s feet. It''s designed specifically for cosmetic use and works by relaxing the underlying muscles.'' On Restylane Lyft: ''Lyft has something unique going for it — it''s one of the only fillers approved for both the midface and hands. If a patient mentions that their hands look older than their face, this is specifically indicated for that.'' The hand indication is a genuine clinical differentiator, not an add-on — some patients seek hand treatment as their primary concern. Be straightforward about Jeuveau: if patients ask how it compares to other neurotoxins, it works through the same mechanism, and the provider can discuss which option fits best. Jeuveau is Evolus and Lyft is Galderma — different loyalty ecosystems.","do_not_say":{"universal":["You need this","Everyone is doing this","This will make you look younger","Guaranteed results","Permanent","This will fix your problem","You''ll look natural","No one will know","This is painless","Zero downtime","Liquid facelift","This is our most popular package"],"pair_specific":["Jeuveau is better than Botox","Lyft will last forever","This will make your hands look 20 years younger","You should do both your face and hands today"],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"That''s expensive — do I really need to treat both?","handling_language":"These are independent treatments for independent concerns. If expression lines are the primary concern, Jeuveau alone addresses that. If you''re also concerned about cheek volume or hands, Lyft is a separate conversation. Your provider can help prioritize based on what''s most important to you.","do_not_say_in_response":"You should do everything at once while you''re here."},{"objection_type":"do_i_need_both","patient_says":"Can''t I just treat my face with Lyft and skip Jeuveau?","handling_language":"Lyft addresses structural volume in the cheeks and hands, not expression lines in the forehead and around the eyes. If the expression lines are a concern, that requires a neurotoxin — filler can''t relax muscles. Your provider can clarify which concerns are which.","do_not_say_in_response":"You really need both or the results won''t be complete."},{"objection_type":"curiosity_about_hands","patient_says":"I didn''t know you could treat hands — is that safe?","handling_language":"Yes — Restylane Lyft has an FDA approval specifically for the dorsal hands. It''s one of the few HA fillers with that specific indication. Your provider can walk you through what''s involved and whether it makes sense for your concerns.","do_not_say_in_response":"It''s totally safe, everyone does it. You''ll love it."}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin (Jeuveau) administered first, filler (Restylane Lyft) second. If sequential visits: Jeuveau 2 weeks before Restylane Lyft. For hand treatment: timing is independent of facial neurotoxin — can be same session without interaction concern.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. Jeuveau retreatment at 3-4 months; Restylane Lyft touch-ups at 12-18 months depending on treatment area.","downtime_note":"Jeuveau: minimal — possible injection-site redness or bruising resolving within hours to a day. Restylane Lyft: possible swelling or bruising, typically 1-2 weeks. Hand treatment: possible bruising and swelling; patients may want to plan around public events.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Jeuveau every 3-4 months (approximately 3 visits per year). Restylane Lyft every 12-18 months. Face and hand treatments can be aligned to the same appointment.","rebooking_trigger":"At your 2-week Jeuveau follow-up, we can assess muscle response. Lyft check-in at 2 weeks. Next Jeuveau appointment in 3-4 months.","next_visit_prompt":"How are the expression lines responding? Any questions about cheek volume or hand results? We''ll plan your next Jeuveau appointment for 3-4 months from now.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754: BoNT-A and HA fillers may be performed together; combination superior to either alone (category-level). FDA label — Jeuveau: prabotulinumtoxinA-xvfs, aesthetics-only indication, Hi-Pure technology. FDA label — Restylane Lyft: NASHA technology, dual indication for midface volume deficit and dorsal hand volume loss in adults over 21. Accepted clinical practice: neurotoxin-first sequencing.","evidence_level":"moderate","review_status":"pending","audience":"staff","patient_safe":true,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
