SELECT
    'pairing_fuel',
    'draft',
    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"xeomin__juvederm_vollure_xc","product_a":"Xeomin","product_b":"Juvederm Vollure XC","patient_facing_name":"Pure Smooth","one_line_positioning":"Xeomin''s pure neurotoxin formulation relaxes expression lines while Vollure smooths nasolabial folds — two different problems, two different solutions.","package_goal":"Treat dynamic expression lines and mid-depth nasolabial fold lines together","ideal_candidate":"Patient experiencing upper-face expression lines alongside nasolabial fold lines; patient who prefers or whose provider recommends a neurotoxin without complexing proteins; patients on long-term multi-product treatment plans where immunogenicity is a provider consideration.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patient with single isolated concern; patients with neurotoxin or HA contraindications.","concern_tags":["dynamic wrinkles","frown lines","crow''s feet","nasolabial folds","facial lines","facial aging"],"why_together":"Xeomin relaxes expression muscles; Vollure smooths nasolabial fold lines with HA gel correction. Neuromodulation cannot address volume-based fold lines, and filler cannot relax dynamic muscles — these mechanisms are complementary and non-overlapping.","A_solves":"Relaxes muscles causing dynamic expression lines (frown lines, crow''s feet, forehead lines)","A_does_not_solve":"Cannot restore lost volume or smooth nasolabial folds","B_adds":"Mid-depth HA correction of nasolabial folds and moderate facial lines (VYCROSS technology, 18-month duration)","clinical_rationale":"Xeomin (incobotulinumtoxinA) is the naked molecule neurotoxin — it contains no complexing proteins (0.55ng vs 4.5ng for Botox), which is a consideration for providers evaluating long-term immunogenicity, as it does not contain accessory proteins. This makes it a consideration for patients planning extended combination therapy. Vollure''s VYCROSS-crosslinked HA addresses nasolabial folds and moderate facial lines with an 18-month duration. The combination treats dynamic expression lines (Xeomin) alongside mid-depth NLF volume loss (Vollure). Xeomin is room-temperature stable, which is a practical advantage for practices. This is a cross-ecosystem pairing (Merz + Allergan). Xeomin maintenance: every 3-4 months. Vollure maintenance: every 12-18 months.","patient_education_summary":"Xeomin is a wrinkle relaxer that''s sometimes described as a ''pure'' or ''naked'' neurotoxin — it contains only the active ingredient without the extra proteins found in some other neurotoxins. Some providers consider this when planning long-term treatment, as it does not contain the accessory proteins found in some other neurotoxins. Vollure is a filler designed specifically for the nasolabial fold lines — those deeper lines from your nose to your mouth — and it typically lasts about 18 months. If you''re noticing both expression lines and those deeper folds, Xeomin addresses the movement-based lines while Vollure addresses the volume-based lines. They work through completely different mechanisms.","staff_close":"Xeomin''s purity is a meaningful differentiator for long-term plans; Vollure is NLF-specific with 18-month duration — two different tools for two different concerns.","staff_talking_points":"Xeomin''s key differentiator is its purity. When explaining: ''Xeomin is sometimes called the naked molecule — it contains only the active toxin without the extra proteins that other neurotoxins have. This may be relevant for patients who plan to use neurotoxin long-term, as it does not contain the accessory proteins found in some other neurotoxins, which some providers consider when long-term immunogenicity is a concern.'' On the Vollure pairing: ''Vollure is specifically designed for the nasolabial fold lines and typically lasts about 18 months. These are different concerns — Xeomin handles the expression lines, Vollure handles the volume loss lines.'' Practical note: Xeomin is room-temperature stable, which is a logistics advantage. This is a cross-brand pairing (Merz + Allergan) — different loyalty programs.","do_not_say":{"universal":["You need this","Everyone is doing this","This will make you look younger","Guaranteed results","Permanent","This will fix your problem","You''ll look natural","No one will know","This is painless","Zero downtime","Liquid facelift","This is our most popular package"],"pair_specific":["Xeomin is better than Botox","Xeomin has no side effects because it''s pure","Vollure will completely eliminate your nasolabial folds","The naked molecule means it lasts longer"],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"do_i_need_both","patient_says":"Why can''t Xeomin treat the lines around my nose too?","handling_language":"Xeomin relaxes muscles that cause expression lines from movement — forehead, frown lines, crow''s feet. The nasolabial folds are different: they deepen partly because of volume loss in the midface, not just muscle movement. Vollure directly corrects that fold with filler placed in the targeted area. These are different mechanisms for different types of lines.","do_not_say_in_response":"You absolutely need both — one won''t be enough."},{"objection_type":"cost","patient_says":"Is Xeomin cheaper than Botox?","handling_language":"Pricing varies by practice and treatment area. What''s more relevant is the clinical fit — Xeomin is selected by some providers for specific patient considerations. Your provider can discuss which neurotoxin is the right choice for your treatment plan.","do_not_say_in_response":"Yes, Xeomin is cheaper and just as good — it''s a bargain."},{"objection_type":"curiosity_about_purity","patient_says":"What does ''naked molecule'' actually mean?","handling_language":"It means Xeomin contains only the active neurotoxin — incobotulinumtoxinA — without the accessory proteins that are present in some other neurotoxins. Some providers consider this when long-term immunogenicity is a concern. Your provider can discuss whether it''s the right consideration for your treatment plan.","do_not_say_in_response":"It means it''s completely pure and has no risks. It''s way better than the alternatives."}],"sequencing_note":"Neurotoxin (Xeomin) administered first, filler (Vollure) second. If sequential visits: Xeomin 2 weeks before Vollure to assess muscle response before addressing static NLF lines. Standard neurotoxin + filler sequencing applies.","timing_note":"Same session or sequential visits. Xeomin retreatment at 3-4 months; Vollure touch-ups at 12-18 months. Some providers consider Xeomin''s lack of accessory proteins relevant for long-term combination plans.","downtime_note":"Xeomin: minimal — possible injection-site redness or bruising resolving within hours to a day. Vollure (NLF): possible swelling or bruising at injection sites, typically resolving within 1-2 weeks.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Xeomin every 3-4 months. Vollure every 12-18 months. Schedules can be aligned — Vollure touch-ups can often coincide with a Xeomin appointment.","rebooking_trigger":"At your 2-week Xeomin follow-up, we can assess muscle response and check on the nasolabial fold area. Next Xeomin appointment in 3-4 months.","next_visit_prompt":"How are the expression lines and the nasolabial fold area looking? We''ll plan your next Xeomin appointment for 3-4 months from now.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1097/DSS.0000000000000754: BoNT-A and HA fillers may be performed together; combination superior to either alone (category-level). FDA label — Xeomin: incobotulinumtoxinA, no accessory proteins, room-temperature stable. FDA label — Juvederm Vollure XC: VYCROSS crosslinking, indicated for moderate to severe facial wrinkles and folds including NLF, 18-month duration. Accepted clinical practice: neurotoxin-first sequencing.","evidence_level":"moderate","review_status":"pending","audience":"staff","patient_safe":true,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
