SELECT
    'pairing_fuel',
    'draft',
    '{"fuel_type":"combination","template_version":"1.0","pair_key":"botox_cosmetic__inmode_morpheus8","product_a":"Botox Cosmetic","product_b":"InMode Morpheus8","patient_facing_name":"Smooth & Tighten","one_line_positioning":"Botox Cosmetic relaxes expression lines while Morpheus8 RF microneedling improves skin texture and firmness — addressing muscle movement and skin quality through separate mechanisms.","package_goal":"Address dynamic expression wrinkles and skin laxity/texture together","ideal_candidate":"Patient experiencing both dynamic expression lines (forehead, crow''s feet, frown lines) and skin quality concerns (laxity, texture, crepiness); patient seeking comprehensive facial rejuvenation beyond wrinkle relaxation alone.","not_ideal_candidate":"Patients with active skin infection, open wounds, or certain skin conditions at the treatment site; patients with pacemakers or metal implants in treatment area (RF device contraindication); patients with single isolated concern.","concern_tags":["dynamic wrinkles","frown lines","crow''s feet","skin laxity","skin texture","collagen loss","facial aging"],"why_together":"Botox Cosmetic relaxes muscles causing expression lines; Morpheus8 targets skin quality, texture, and laxity through RF microneedling. Neuromodulation cannot tighten loose skin or improve skin texture — energy devices cannot relax expression muscles. Published evidence supports same-day safety of this combination.","A_solves":"Relaxes muscles causing dynamic expression lines (frown lines, crow''s feet, forehead lines)","A_does_not_solve":"Cannot tighten loose skin or improve skin texture","B_adds":"RF microneedling-driven collagen remodeling improving skin texture, firmness, and laxity at different tissue layers than neurotoxin","clinical_rationale":"Morpheus8 RF microneedling improves skin texture, tightens skin, and stimulates collagen through controlled thermal energy in the dermis and subdermal layers. Botox Cosmetic controls dynamic wrinkles through muscle relaxation. These target fundamentally different tissue layers and aging mechanisms — Morpheus8 addresses skin quality that neurotoxin cannot improve, while Botox Cosmetic addresses movement-based lines that energy devices cannot treat. Multi-modality stacking protocols in accepted clinical practice place energy devices and neurotoxin as complementary layers in comprehensive treatment. Published safety data (DOI 10.1111/j.1524-4725.2005.31105) supports no decrease in neurotoxin efficacy when combined with RF devices.","patient_education_summary":"Morpheus8 uses radiofrequency energy to improve your skin''s texture, firmness, and overall quality from within. Botox Cosmetic addresses a completely different issue — the lines caused by muscle movement, like crow''s feet and frown lines. Energy treatments can''t relax muscles, and Botox can''t tighten skin. When both concerns are present, addressing them through different approaches can create a more complete improvement.","staff_close":"Energy device for skin quality and firmness; neurotoxin for expression lines — different tissue layers, different tools, supported by published combination safety data.","staff_talking_points":"When a patient wants comprehensive facial rejuvenation, explain that there are multiple layers to aging. ''Morpheus8 works on your skin quality — improving texture, firmness, and stimulating new collagen. Botox Cosmetic works on the dynamic lines caused by muscle movement. Think of it as addressing the skin itself and the muscles underneath it separately. We typically do the energy treatment first to improve the skin foundation, then address the movement lines.'' This is about treating different problems, not adding treatments for the sake of adding them.","do_not_say":{"universal":["You need this","Everyone is doing this","This will make you look younger","Guaranteed results","Permanent","This will fix your problem","You''ll look natural","No one will know","This is painless","Zero downtime","Liquid facelift","This is our most popular package"],"pair_specific":["Morpheus8 will tighten your skin permanently","This combination will replace a surgical facelift","The RF won''t affect your Botox at all","You''ll need fewer Botox treatments after Morpheus8"],"practice_specific":[]},"top_objections":[{"objection_type":"do_i_need_both","patient_says":"Why can''t I just do Botox for everything?","handling_language":"Botox Cosmetic addresses lines caused by muscle movement — forehead lines, frown lines, crow''s feet. It can''t tighten skin that has become lax or improve the texture and quality of the skin itself. Morpheus8 addresses those skin quality concerns through a completely different mechanism. If you have both types of concerns, they require different approaches.","do_not_say_in_response":"You really need both or you won''t see the full result."},{"objection_type":"downtime","patient_says":"I can''t have much downtime — is this realistic?","handling_language":"Botox Cosmetic has minimal downtime — possible redness or bruising at injection sites for a day. Morpheus8 has more noticeable social downtime — redness, swelling, and pinpoint marks typically lasting several days. They can be scheduled separately if you want to space out the recovery periods. Your provider can discuss timing based on your schedule.","do_not_say_in_response":"Don''t worry, the downtime is nothing. You''ll be fine by tomorrow."},{"objection_type":"fear_of_rf_interaction","patient_says":"Will the RF treatment affect how the Botox works?","handling_language":"Published evidence shows no decrease in neurotoxin efficacy when combined with RF devices. The standard approach is to do Morpheus8 first, then Botox Cosmetic, which is how providers sequence this in practice. Your provider follows this protocol to ensure both treatments perform as expected.","do_not_say_in_response":"There''s no interaction at all — they''re completely unrelated."}],"sequencing_note":"Energy device (Morpheus8) first, neurotoxin (Botox Cosmetic) after. If same day: Morpheus8 first, then neurotoxin after assessment. If sequential: Morpheus8 first, Botox Cosmetic 1-2 weeks later when inflammation has resolved.","timing_note":"Energy-first sequencing. Maintenance: Morpheus8 2-3x per year; Botox Cosmetic every 3-4 months.","downtime_note":"Botox Cosmetic: minimal — possible injection-site redness or bruising, hours to a day. Morpheus8: several days of social downtime — redness, swelling, pinpoint bleeding marks. Patients should plan around events. If same session, cumulative recovery should be discussed.","same_session_ok":true,"maintenance_story":"Botox Cosmetic every 3-4 months. Morpheus8 typically 2-3 sessions in an initial series, then maintenance 1-2x per year. Schedules do not align — Morpheus8 is less frequent than neurotoxin maintenance.","rebooking_trigger":"At your 2-week Botox Cosmetic follow-up, we can assess expression line results. Morpheus8 check-in at 4-6 weeks post-treatment. Discuss timing of next session in Morpheus8 series.","next_visit_prompt":"How are the expression lines and skin texture looking? We''ll plan your next Botox Cosmetic appointment for 3-4 months from now and discuss Morpheus8 series timing.","source_support_summary":"PubMed DOI 10.1111/j.1524-4725.2005.31105: No decrease in BoNT-A efficacy when combined with RF device within 10 minutes; validates same-day RF + BoNT-A safety. FDA clearance — Botox Cosmetic: glabellar lines, lateral canthal lines, forehead lines in adults. FDA clearance — InMode Morpheus8: 510(k)-cleared for subdermal coagulation and ablation of soft tissue via RF microneedling. Accepted clinical practice: multi-modality stacking (energy device followed by neurotoxin) is established.","evidence_level":"strong","review_status":"pending","audience":"staff","patient_safe":true,"last_reviewed":null,"reviewed_by":null}'::jsonb,
